title: barbecue
directions: Cook on low in crock-pot all day or night.
Add 1/2 bottle barbecue sauce.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix and chill for several hours.
Form into buckeye-size balls and dip into chocolate coating.

title: helen's scalloped oysters
directions: In sprayed 2-quart casserole, place alternate layers of oysters with liquid and crackers, dotting each layer with butter and sprinkling with salt and pepper.
End with layer of crumbs. Add milk until liquid almost reaches top of casserole.
Dot with remaining butter.
Bake at 350° until browned, about 45 minutes.

title: grama's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream together brown sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Add nuts, chocolate chips, coconut and oatmeal.
Form into balls.
Dip tops in sugar and put on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Blend butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and chill. Roll into small balls.
Bake at 300° until done.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: sunday rolls
directions: Dissolve the yeast in warm water.
Let sit 5 minutes until bubbly.
Mix the hot water, honey, oil and salt until the honey is completely dissolved.
Add eggs.
Stir well.
Add the yeast.
Add the flour.
Mix well.
If the dough is to be used immediately, add 1/2 cup more flour.
Shape the dough into any type rolls.
Allow to rise.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 425°.
This dough is more easily handled after chilling until firm, then shape the dough into rolls. Allow to rise.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 425°.
After shaping, raw rolls may be frozen.
Allow 3 hours from freezer to oven.
Yield: 2 dozen rolls.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Whisk the vinegar, oil, parsley, mint, salt and pepper in a large bowl until smooth.
Add sliced cucumber and green onion; toss to coat.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a pie plate. Dip the tomatoes slices in mixture to coat both sides.
In a 12-inch skillet, over medium heat, in the butter or margarine or bacon drippings, fry tomato slices, a few at a time, until golden brown and crisp on both sides. Add more butter as needed.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Cut up marshmallows and mix with pineapple.
Let stand until soft and add nuts and whipped cream.
Chill before serving.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Toss lightly.
Place mixture in casserole.
Pour 2 cups milk over top.
Sprinkle with paprika and 2 tablespoons buttered bread crumbs.
Bake on 400° about 35 minutes or until browned.

title: ground beef and potato casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain.
Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes to 1 hour.
Extra water may be added, if needed.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: layered spinach salad
directions: In a large salad bowl (not too deep), put layer of spinach, onion, peas and ham.
Cover with dressing.
Repeat the layering, covering each with dressing.

title: kokekola cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour; set aside.
In a saucepan, bring to boil and stir constantly butter, vegetable oil, cocoa and Coke.
Stir in marshmallows.
Pour this mixture over flour and sugar mix.
Add buttermilk, eggs, baking soda and vanilla flavoring.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.
Check at 30 minutes with toothpick.
Do not overcook.

title: green dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Microwave for 2 minutes.
Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: cucumber salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled, about 2 hours.
May serve with grilled fish, poached or grilled chicken or tortilla chips.
Yield: 3 cups.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, stir together 1 cup sugar and cornstarch. Gradually stir in water until smooth.
Stir in egg yolks.
Stirring constantly, bring to boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Stir in next 3 ingredients.
Cool.
Turn into pastry shell.
In small bowl with mixer at high speed, beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually beat in 1/3 cup sugar.
Continue beating until stiff peaks form.
Spread over meringue.
Bake in oven until lightly brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: black bean tortilla casserole
directions: Prepare black beans as directed on package (wash, sort, bring to
boil).
Cook
with
onion
and 1/2 green pepper (chopped) in
pot.
Cook
down
then
rinse
beans, set aside. Saute the rest
of
onion and pepper in butter; set aside, mix with the beans.
Layer
tortillas
in
casserole sprayed with Pam. Alternate
tortillas
with
beans, salsa, sour cream and cheese; top
with remaining salsa and cheese.
Bake covered 20 minutes in 375° oven.

title: hot sauce
directions: Simmer brown sugar and water; add the rest of the ingredients and cook slowly for about 1 hour.
Stir often.

title: sugar-free trifle
directions: You will also need a deep bowl (trifle bowl).

title: aunt connie's stew
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Brown ground beef and onions. Drain.
Stir all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Cook in a slow cooker for 3 hours on high.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars until very creamy. Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and blend well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by the teaspoonful on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cut cooked potatoes in 1/8-inch slices; sprinkle salt, pepper, mustard, sugar and flour.
Heat water and vinegar to boiling.
Put bacon, sliced and chopped fine, in skillet; fry light brown.
Add onion and brown.
Add potatoes and hot vinegar; heat to absorb vinegar and serve warm.

title: rum cake
directions: While the cake is baking, take butter and melt in a saucepan. Add water and sugar. Boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Allow to cool and stir in rum. Remove the cake from the oven and set on a rack to cool. When cool, invert onto a serving plate. Prick the top of the cake (where the chopped pecans layer is) and drizzle the glaze evenly over the top, allowing it to soak into the cake.

title: marinated carrots
directions: After cooking fresh or frozen broccoli, drain and serve with this easy delicious sauce:

title: lasagna
directions: Brown together the ground beef and onion, then add the remaining ingredients. Simmer about 2 hours. Add water as needed.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need a flowerpot, silk flowers and planting shovel.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Cook and drain sausage, remove crust and cube bread.
Slightly beat eggs.
Mix sausage, eggs and bread together.
Add cheese. Mix milk, salt and mustard; add to other ingredients by pouring over the top in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate for at least 12 hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes (until browned on top).

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Spread in pan. Bake until golden brown, 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares or pour into prepared pie shell for quiche.
Makes 6 servings.

title: jazzy yams
directions: Boil scrubbed yams until tender, about 35 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Peel.
Mash yams and add all remaining ingredients except pecans.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into a buttered 6 c. baking dish and bake 45 minutes at 350 degrees.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Serves 8.

title: cream of spinach soup
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat until smooth and bubbly.
Add chicken broth.
Cook until thickened.
Add spinach.
Cook briefly until spinach is broken up. Pour into blender and blend.
Pour back into pan, add cream and heat.
Do not boil.
Sprinkle with croutons.
Serve very hot.

title: pickled cabbage
directions: Layer.
Shred cabbage and place half in bowl.
Shred onion and place half in bowl; sprinkle sugar (1/2 on the bottom and 1/2 on the top).
Heat the vinegar, salad oil, sugar, dry mustard and celery seed together.
Pour hot mixture over all and seal with lid. Keeps 2 weeks in refrigerator.
Freezes indefinitely.
Salad also good on hot dogs.

title: sweet potato apple-raisin salad
directions: Peel the sweet potatoes and cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Place sweet potatoes in a medium size microwave-safe dish.
Add 1/3 cup water.
Cover and cook on High 8 to 10 minutes, stirring halfway through cooking. Drain.
Set aside to cool for about 15 minutes.

title: maple salad dressing for fruit
directions: Beat the yolk of an egg and place in double boiler. Add the maple syrup and cook until thickened, about 1 minute.
Fold in lemon juice and whipped cream. Serve with fruit salads.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in a loaf pan 7 x 11 inches. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Cover top of meat loaf with additional catsup while cooking.

title: ratatouille
directions: Heat 1/4 cup olive oil in large cast-iron skillet.
Slowly add the vegetables, stirring to mix.
Cook on low heat until tender. Add basil, parsley and pepper to taste.
Add oil as needed.
May be served hot or cold.

title: hidden sloppy joe
directions: Cook and stir beef and onion.
Drain. Stir in catsup, mustard and soup.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat. Simmer 5 minutes. Heat oven to 375°.
Grease Bundt pan.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Beat 30 seconds.
Spread 2 cups batter in bottom and 2-inches up side and center of pan.
Spoon beef onto center of batter.
Drop remaining batter by spoonfuls 1/2-inch apart.
Bake until light brown and firm, about 25 minutes.
Invert on heatproof plate.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of loaf pan.
Mix sugar, pumpkin, oil, vanilla and eggs in a large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes. Cool on wire rack.

title: fried catfish
directions: Blend eggs and milk.
Dip fish in egg batter and roll in corn meal.
Put fish in heavy frypan which has 1/8 inch melted fat (but not smoking).
Fry at moderate heat.
Cooking Time:
10 minutes (depending on size of fish).
Drain on paper.

title: dream easy salad
directions: Mix pudding, Jell-O and water in saucepan.
Boil 1 minute and let cool.
Drain fruit and stir into cooled mixture.
Add Cool Whip.

title: salmon and capalenni pasta
directions: Cook pasta until just tender. Drizzle with oil and toss in dill. Place on parchment paper. Top with salmon. Spread mustard on salmon. Top with asparagus. Wrap up and bake in a 400 degree oven for 10-15 minutes.

title: white chocolate berry cream pie
directions: Pour milk into medium bowl.
Add pudding mixes.
Beat with wire whisk 1 minute.
Gently stir in whipped topping and lemon peel. Spoon strawberries into bottom of crust; top with pudding mixture. Refrigerate four hours or until set.

title: oatmeal blueberry muffins(cholesterol-free)
directions: Mix oats with milk; let stand 5 minutes.
Add oil and egg whites to oatmeal mixture.
Blend together the dry ingredients and then add to oatmeal mixture.
Add blueberries.
(Use cupcake liners; makes 8 to 9 large muffins.)
Bake at 350° for approximately 12 minutes or until lightly browned and knife comes out clean.

title: pecan delights
directions: In large saucepan, combine first four ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Gradually add milk and stir well.
Continue cooking until candy thermometer reads 248° (firm ball stage).
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Fold in pecans. Drop by tablespoon on well buttered cookie sheet.
Chill until firm.
Melt chocolate chips and shortening in a microwave-safe bowl or double boiler.
Dip each cluster.
Cool.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: sweet potato chips(fat-free)
directions: Arrange slices in a circle around outer edge of a plate.
Cook on High 4 to 5 minutes until dry for 12 slices.
Rotate plate halfway through cooking.
Let stand 1 minute.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Blend cheese and other ingredients in food processor until mixed well.
Chill until firm.
Shape into ball; roll in pecans. Chill.

title: lemon love notes
directions: Mix butter, 1 cup flour and 1 cup sugar.
Press into an ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes or until golden. Combine confectioners sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and baking powder; add eggs, lemon juice and peel and pour evenly over baked, cooled mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cut in squares.

title: lemon-sweet cucumber
directions: In large bowl, combine sugar, salt, dill weed, lemon peel, vinegar and lemon juice; blend well.
Add cucumber slices; toss to coat.
Cover.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.
If desired, drain before serving.
Makes 8 1/4 cups.

title: cran-waldorf salad
directions: Heat 1 cup cranberry juice to boiling in a small pan.
Add gelatin to dissolve.
Add the remaining juice and the salt. Chill until partially set.
Stir in apple, celery and nuts.
Pour into individual molds or loaf pan that has been oiled.
Unmold onto pineapple slices and top with a teaspoon of mayonnaise.

title: hawaiian pound cake
directions: Mix in order listed.
Beat eggs, sugar, shortening (I use butter-flavored shortening), milk, flour, baking powder, salt and lemon flavoring until creamy.
Turn mixer on fold and fold in crushed pineapple and coconut.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Combine soups, chilies and onion.
Layer torn tortillas and soup mixture, chicken and cheese alternately in casserole pan and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: jiffy cobbler
directions: Pour pie filling into 8 or 9-inch square glass cake pan. Sprinkle cake mix over pie filling.
Melt butter and pour on top. Sprinkle on nuts (if desired).
Bake at 350° for 35 or 40 minutes.

title: easy hot spiced cider
directions: Simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove the stick cinnamon and cloves. Serve in punch cups.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet and drain off fat.
Add spaghetti sauce to beef.
Let simmer.
Cook spaghetti and drain.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish, sprayed with Pam so it won't stick, layer 1/2 of spaghetti, meat sauce and 1/2 package each of the cheeses. Repeat layer.
Bake at 375° until cheese is melted and brown.

title: carrot-raisin salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; cover and chill 2 to 3 hours.
Serves 6.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Roll out and cut in strips.
Put in chicken broth. Be sure the chicken broth is at a rolling boil when you put the dumplings in.

title: grandma's 1, 2, 3, 4 cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until smooth.
Add milk, eggs and flour, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baking pans and bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh raisin pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients well.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell and bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: fish fritters
directions: Mix the sardines, egg and bread crumbs together.
Add the rest of the ingredients and form into flat cakes and brown on each side in a nonstick skillet coated with 1 teaspoon of olive oil.
Makes 12 small or 6 large cakes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Mix soup and milk together and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients together in large bowl.
Form patties and brown. Layer in casserole, pouring soup and milk mixture on each patty. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended and refrigerate overnight to allow flavors to blend.

title: brownies
directions: Cream together the margarine and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs. Mix cocoa and flour together and add to first mixture.
Add nut meats.
Pour into greased baking pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Makes 2 dozen brownies.

title: lace cookies
directions: Put oats, flour, sugar and salt in a bowl.
Pour hot melted butter over mixture.
Add eggs, vanilla and pecans.
Cover a cookie sheet with foil.
Drop 1/2 teaspoon batter two inches apart on foil.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 325°.
When cookies are cool, foil will peel off.
Be sure cookies are brown around edges.
If not, they will be chewy.
They should be crisp when cool.
(The batter will be very thin.)

title: honey almond cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter two cookie sheets.
Heat butter and honey in a medium saucepan, stirring occasionally over medium heat until butter is melted.
Stir in sugar.
Cool 5 minutes.
Add egg whites and vanilla, stirring until well blended.
Stir in flour, salt and almonds until well blended.
Drop batter by tablespoon onto prepared cookie sheet, 3 cookies per sheet. Spread in 4-inch circles.
Bake 5 to 6 minutes, until edges are golden.
Cool on cookie sheet on a wire rack.

title: apricot orange jello salad
directions: Drain apricots; reserve syrup.
Puree apricots.
Combine syrup and salt and heat to boiling point.
Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Add balance of ingredients.
Mix well.
Finally slowly add 7-Up around sides so it will not boil over.
Pour into mold. When set, makes 12 servings.

title: amazing coconut pie(for pastry-making haters!)
directions: Combine milk, sugar and Bisquick.
Mix eggs, butter and vanilla.
Combine and beat on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased pie pan and let stand for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Bake 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: sour cream softies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients and add alternately with sour cream.
Blend well. Drop by tablespoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
If desired, sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar before baking.

title: roman holiday
directions: Saute peppers, onion and garlic in butter or oil. Remove this and brown meat very lightly. Stir peppers and onions into beef. Add noodles, soup and sauces and most of the grated cheese.
Cook in greased casserole and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with graham cracker crust. Reserve 1/2 cup crumbs.
Slice bananas and place in layer over crust. Slice ice cream into thick slices and place over bananas until it is level with the top of the pan. Sprinkle with walnuts and freeze until firm.
Melt chocolate chips, butter, sugar and milk. Cook until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Cool chocolate and pour over ice cream.
Freeze until firm.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Roll into small balls, then roll in sugar.
Do not flatten.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken tahitian
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Stir soup mix, cornstarch, reserved pineapple juice and lime juice.
Arrange chicken and pineapple chunks in 2-quart baking dish.
Pour onion mixture over chicken and bake for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.

title: steak and dumplings
directions: Pound flour into round or chuck steak.
Cut into serving pieces.
Brown; put into casserole and pour soup and water over meat.
Cover.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours or until tender.
Water may be added if needed.

title: forgotten chicken
directions: Place chicken in bottom of a large baking dish.
Mix rice, celery soup, onion soup mix and milk and pour over chicken. Cover with foil and bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water (2 cups).
Mix butter in flour and add yeast and more water as needed to make a stiff dough. Cover and let rise to double in size.
Let rise 3 or 4 more times and work down.
Grease hands and pan.
Roll out in circles and quarter.
Fry in deep, smoking hot grease.

title: sophisticated meat balls
directions: Combine all ingredients except soup and cream cheese.
Shape into balls and brown in oil.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Remove balls; pour off drippings.
Stir in soup and cream cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: broiled crab meltaways
directions: Slice each muffin in half and cut each half into four. Arrange on two cookie trays.
Put the crab meat in your colander and rinse with cold water; drain well on paper towels.
Mix the remaining ingredients in the small bowl of your mixer.
Mix all of this well; add crab and spread on muffin quarters.
You must then freeze these at least 30 minutes.
Will keep for weeks.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: In a heavy skillet, cook beef with vegetables until meat is done and vegetables are tender; drain excess fat.
Pour meat mixture into a 9-inch square baking pan.
Combine soup and mix; mix well and pour over meat mixture.
Place Tater Tots on top and bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle French fried onions on top of Tater Tots and return to the oven for 10 minutes longer.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: jam pockets
directions: Cream shortening, cheese and salt until smooth.
Gradually stir in flour and mix until well blended.
Divide dough into thirds and chill for several hours.
Roll out dough on floured surface to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut with 2 1/2-inch round cutter.

title: picante chicken
directions: Place chicken in a greased shallow 2-quart baking dish. In a small bowl, combine picante sauce, brown sugar and mustard. Pour over chicken. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes or until chicken juices run clear. Serve over rice, if desired.

title: divine sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine and
sugar.
Add
egg
and vanilla; mix well. Stir in
flour,
cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Chill dough; roll teaspoonful in hands;	flatten on ungreased cookie sheet with small glass
dipped in sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with the skins on, let cool and then peel.
Boil eggs and then peel.
Chop potatoes into small pieces, about the size of a dime or less.
Chop boiled eggs.
Cut celery and onion into very small pieces.
Add all of these ingredients together and then add the Miracle Whip (a little at a time), vinegar, mustard, sugar and salt. You may need to add more or less of these ingredients according to taste.
Do not stir with your hands or use a mixer.

title: mints(for weddings or showers)
directions: Knead.
When you feel like giving up it will go together.
Use paste food color to make mints desired color.
Form into small balls.
Roll in superfine granulated sugar.
Press into molds, dump out and dry overnight.
Store in airtight containers.
Will keep fresh for several weeks.
Can be frozen.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until thick. Stir remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 2 greased large loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: chocolate banana pie
directions: Microwave chocolate, 2 tablespoons milk and margarine on High, stirring frequently, until chocolate is melted.
Spread over crust and refrigerate until firm.
Then place banana slices over chocolate.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Cut fryer up.
Place in baking dish with a small amount of water to keep chicken from drying out.
Cook about 20 minutes at 325°.
Turn over and cook about 20 minutes more.
Remove from pan and dip in sauce.
Put back in oven and cook about 15 to 20 minutes, or until tender.
Baking time may vary, depending on chicken.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cocoa and salt together.
Mix egg yolks and milk.
Cook until thickened.
Add vanilla and butter.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: antipasto party tray
directions: Combine olive oil, vinegar, water, Italian seasoning, black pepper and garlic in a glass jar.
Cover tightly and shake well. Pour mixture over vegetables.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator for at least 30 minutes.
Arrange alternately on a serving tray.

title: hamburger corn casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add onion and cook until tender but not brown.
Add corn, soups, sour cream, pimento, salt and pepper. Mix well with noodles.
Put into 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 12 people.

title: mexi-chili casserole
directions: Save 1 cup chips and 1/2 cup cheese.
Combine rest of chips, cheese and chili and both sauces and pour into casserole dish. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Spread top with sour cream.
Sprinkle the rest of cheese and crushed corn chips over sour cream.
Bake for 5 more minutes.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat together cream cheese and butter.
Add vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Slowly add sugar, beating until smooth. Covers two 8 or 9-inch cake.
Cover; store in refrigerator.

title: monkey bread
directions: Spray bundt pan with cooking spray.
Mix together, sugar and cinnamon.
Cut each biscuit into 4 small pieces, and roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture, being sure to cover well.
Layer coated biscuits in bundt pan.
Mix remaining sugar and cinnamon with melted butter and pour over biscuits.
Top with pecans if desired. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: While potatoes are warm, pour dressing over them.
Chill for 2 hours.
Add celery and onion.
Chop egg whites.
Add mashed yolks (reserve some for garnish).
Combine rest of yolk with mayonnaise, sour cream and horseradish.
Fold into salad.
Add salt to taste. Celery seed can be added.

title: buttered crab
directions: Mash anchovy fillets; work in bread crumbs and nutmeg.
Add wine and season to taste.
Then bring gently to the boil in a saucepan and simmer for 5 minutes.
Flake the meat from the crabs; mix with the melted butter and add to the hot wine mixture.
Cook gently for 4 minutes, then serve on a hot dish surrounded by strips of buttered toast.
Serve with a side salad of your choice.

title: perfect waffles
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Put eggs into small bowl and beat on high speed one minute.
Add milk and vanilla to eggs, then add to dry ingredients.
Beat on medium speed 1 1/2 minutes.
Add oil; beat on low speed until blended.
Makes 4 full size (4 section) waffles.
Baked waffles freeze well.

title: herbed potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes about 1/4-inch thick.
Arrange potato and onion slices in the microwave dish.
Combine water, margarine and herb; pour over top.
Cook, covered, on High 10 to 12 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir before serving.

title: glorified rice
directions: Drain pineapple, measuring syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 1/4 cups.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Add salt.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add cherries and pineapple.
Chill thoroughly.
Combine cream and sugar.
Whip. Fold whipped cream into rice.

title: fruit smoothie
directions: Combine orange juice, banana (or other fruit), milk, water and honey in container of electric blender.
Cover and blend at high speed until thick and smooth, about 1 minute.
Add ice cubes, one at a time, and blend until smooth and frothy.
Great summertime drink for kids.

title: snack mix
directions: Mix all ingredients, except for chocolate.
Slowly melt chocolate, then pour over other ingredients.
Mix.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Refrigerate.
Break into small pieces.

title: creamy fruit dip
directions: Mix and serve with fresh strawberries or other fruit.

title: black cherry cheese frozen pie
directions: Toast coconut in margarine over low heat for 20 minutes, stirring often.
Spoon ice cream into crust.
Place chopped pecans over ice cream, forming another layer.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar and put over pecan layer.
Put toasted coconut over cream cheese topping, placing a cherry in the middle for garnish.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix eggs, vegetable oil and water.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake in two loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mashed potato patties
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Pour out on floured foil. Make patties; fry in corn oil until browned on both sides. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: peanut cookies
directions: Mix
all ingredients.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheets; flatten as you drop.
Bake for 7 to 10 minutes at 424°.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Chop lettuce and put in large bowl.
Top with onion, celery and peas.
Mix sour cream with mayonnaise and layer on top of peas.
Sprinkle sugar on sour cream mixture.
Layer cheese and sprinkle with bacon bits.

title: pumpkin oat muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl and blend well.
Add to dry ingredients and stir just enough to moisten.
Sprinkle top of individual muffins with 1/2 cup packed brown sugar, 1/4 teaspoon pumpkin pie spice, 1 tablespoon flour and cut in 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake in greased muffin tins at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix pineapple, juice and all, into soda; set aside . Sift flour, sugar and salt together.
Add pineapple mixture and bananas; stir by hand.
Add eggs and stir.
Add nuts.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool and top with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: seashell pasta salad
directions: In a large bowl, stir together all ingredients until well mixed.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour before serving.
Makes 10 cups of salad.

title: angel food candy
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup and vinegar. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves. Cook without stirring until the temperature reaches 300° (hard crack stage) on a candy thermometer.
Do not overcook.
Remove from the heat and quickly stir in baking soda.
Pour into a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Do not spread candy; mixture will not fill pan.
When cool, break into bite-size pieces.
Dip into melted chocolate; place on waxed paper until the chocolate is firm.
Store candy tightly covered.
Yield:
1 1/2 pounds.

title: creamed corn casserole
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients over low heat and then put in greased baking dish.
Melt the butter and mix with the 1/4 cup bread crumbs.
Put on top of casserole and bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 325°.

title: lemon squares
directions: Melt butter.
Mix in powdered sugar and flour.
Put into square glass baking dish and bake about 10 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini crescent pie
directions: Line 8-inch pie pan with crescent triangles.
Spread with mustard.
Cook zucchini and onion with seasonings until tender.

title: buttercream drops
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs and beat well.
Mix flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add the dry ingredients alternately with sour cream and creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: reese cups
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and chill.
Roll into small balls.
Stick balls with toothpicks.
Chill again.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in a double boiler.
Dip chilled balls in chocolate mixture and set on wax paper to harden.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes in 1/4-inch slices.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and dredge in cornmeal.
Heat oil in heavy skillet and fry tomatoes over medium heat until browned, turning once.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients except last 2.
Roll mixture into balls and roll in 3 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon. Bake 10 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix sugar, butter and syrup together.
Boil for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Take off heat and stir in salt and vanilla.
Now pour over popped (hot air) popcorn in large metal pan and toss until corn is well covered with syrup.
Bake for 1 hour at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.
Put a baking sheet under dish pan. Pour when done on wax paper to cool.

title: funnel cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Fry in vegetable oil for 1 minute on each side.
Sprinkle top with 10x powdered sugar.
Makes about 1 dozen.

title: peach or cherry crisp
directions: Put in greased dish and bake at 375°.

title: cheese cake tarts
directions: Cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time. add vanilla.
Fill small foil liners for miniature cupcake pans 3/4 full.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions and put in casserole dish.
Add green beans, soup and milk.
Stir together, then add Tater Tots to the top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pink punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and water.
Add Hi-C and pineapple juice. Freeze.

title: banana-orange slush
directions: Combine water, orange juice, ice cubes and banana in container of electric blender; process until smooth.
Combine orange juice mixture and ginger ale; stir gently.
Yields 5 cups.

title: cold fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill for several hours or overnight. Goes well with beef tips or ham.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant and slice.
Dip slices in egg and cracker crumbs and fry in a little oil until brown on both sides; drain on paper towel.
Place slices in a large flat casserole dish.
Lay a slice of tomato on top of each slice of eggplant, then lay a slice of American cheese on top of each tomato.* Place in a 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: zesty carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender in salted water; drain well.

Place carrot strips in greased baking dish. Add 2 tablespoons water in which carrots were cooked. This keeps them moist while baking. Mix the next 4 ingredients and spread over carrots. Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: spaghetti with cottage cheese pesto
directions: For Pesto:
In blender container, combine spinach, water, cottage cheese, basil, Parmesan cheese, oil and garlic.
Cover and process until smooth.
Spoon half of pesto over half of hot cooked pasta.
Toss well.
Add remaining pasta and pesto.
Toss again until well mixed.
Serve immediately.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: baked cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower until tender (10 minutes).
Drain.
Add butter, bread crumbs and grated cheese.
Put in casserole and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until hot.

title: taco soup
directions: Mix altogether; bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Can be topped with grated cheese, chips or sour cream.

title: scrambled egg bake
directions: Use an 8 x 8 pan (oiled).
Put dry dressing mix in pan and sprinkle with cheese.
Beat eggs, half and half and seasonings. Pour carefully over dressing and cheese.
Top with cooled sausage crumbs.
Refrigerate over night.
Bake at 350, uncovered about 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes and serve.

title: butter mints(diabetic recipe)
directions: Cream together the margarine, milk and butter flavoring until fluffy.
Stir in sugar replacement.
Knead or work with hands until smooth.
Roll into small, marble size balls; press each ball firmly into mold.
Unmold onto waxed paper.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Bake muffins as directed on package.
Crumble 1/2 of muffins in bottom of bowl.
Layer tomatoes, pepper and onions (all vegetables are chopped).
Add chopped ham.
Mix pickle relish with mayonnaise.
Cover salad with mayonnaise mixture.
Top off with remaining muffins, crumbled.
Refrigerate overnight, covered.

title: mandarin chicken
directions: Cut chicken breast into strips.
Slice zucchini and celery. Saute chicken, then set aside.
Break up noodles.
Cook in 1 cup of water with zucchini and celery slices for five minutes.
Stir in chicken, flavor packet and sweet and sour sauce.
Heat thoroughly.
Top each serving with mandarin oranges.
Serves four.

title: switchel or ginger water
directions: Mix all of the ingredients, then add enough cold water to make one gallon.
This makes a good thirst quencher on hot summer days.

title: chicken creast
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Cool, take chicken off the bones. Roll out biscuits.
Put chicken and cheese into biscuits.
Roll it up.
Pour soup and milk over the biscuits.
Bake at 375° to 400°, until biscuits are done all the way.

title: dill dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a blender.
By omitting the milk it will make a great vegetable dip.

title: pecan chicken(serves 8)
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Mix together egg and buttermilk.
Dip chicken in egg mixture and then coat in flour mixture.
Melt butter in baking dish.
Place chicken in dish, turning once to coat with butter.
Sprinkle with coarsely chopped pecans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: red devil's food cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Add alternately with flour and sour milk.
Make a paste of the cocoa and red food coloring and add.
Then add the vanilla and pinch of salt.
Mix together vinegar and soda.
Add last.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Layer in order in large glass bowl.
Mix dressing by directions on package.
Pour over salad.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat 3 eggs in mixer bowl until thick and lemon colored.
Add sugar gradually, beating until smooth.
Add pumpkin and lemon juice; mix well.
Fold in flour, baking powder and pumpkin pie spice.
Spoon into greased 10 x 15-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Invert onto towel sprinkled with confectioners sugar.
Roll up in towel as for jelly roll. Cool.
Beat cream cheese with remaining ingredients in mixer bowl.
Unroll cake.
Spread with cream cheese mixture; re-roll to enclose filling.
Chill until serving time.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening. Break eggs. Add one at a time and beat well. Add pumpkin and stir. Add sifted dry ingredients and stir until moistened. Do not overmix. Bake in 2 loaf pans, greased and floured, at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Place raw broccoli flowerets in bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Toss all ingredients together.

title: joni's cookies
directions: Combine eggs, milk and oil. Add to dry ingredients. Stir in chips. Form into small balls. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: peanut cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugars.
Beat in eggs.
Combine flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Stir into creamed mixture. Add the oats and peanuts.
Drop by heaping tablespoonful onto greased baking sheets.
Dip the bottom of a glass in sugar and slightly flatten cookies.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes. Yields 4 dozen.

title: hawaiian pineapple cheese mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: icebox pickles(5 days)
directions: Bring the water and salt to a boil, then let cool.
Add the vinegar, garlic, dill and grape leaves.
Put in large jar (I use gallon jar and medium size pickles).
Wash and clean cucumbers. Place everything in jar, then pour mixture over pickles and put lid on jar.
Place in refrigerator.
Can eat in 5 days.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix strawberries in Cool Whip.
Put pecans on top or any other icing that you like.

title: harvard beets
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add cider vinegar and water; boil for 5 minutes.
Add beets and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Add butter and season with salt and pepper.

title: old-fashioned real pie crust(easy to make)
directions: Add ice water to beaten egg and vinegar to make 1/2 cup liquid. In a bowl of mixer, put all dry ingredients; mix together.
Add lard and mix on low speed.
Pour egg-vinegar mixture in slowly. When all mixed, divide into 4 balls and refrigerate.
Makes 4 pie crusts.

title: boiled raisin spice cake
directions: Cover raisins with water and simmer 20 minutes.
Drain, saving liquid.
Add enough cold water to make 1 cup.
Coat raisins with flour to keep them from sinking to the bottom of cake.

title: dill pickles
directions: Place small cucumbers in sterile quart jars.
Bring ingredients to boil and pour over pickles and let set 10 minutes.
Pour off and bring back to boil.
Put sprig of dill on top of pickles.
Pour brine over pickles again and seal with hot lids.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, butter, milk and salt.
Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Go sort of fast, may start to harden.
Drop in cookie size on wax paper until hard.

title: chile chicken burritos
directions: Lightly mix chicken, green chiles, onions, cheese, sour cream and salt.
Spread about 1/2 down the center of each tortilla, then roll it into a cylinder.
Wrap lightly in a paper towel and heat in the microwave oven 30 to 45 seconds for each burrito until filling is bubbling.
Let stand 1 minute before serving.
Serves 6.

title: special apple squares
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt as for a pie crust.
Blend in sour cream.
Knead until all flour is absorbed.
Chill dough in refrigerator for at least one
hour.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Mix together mincemeat, sugar, butter and egg.
Add flour, salt, baking soda, nutmeats and butterscotch morsels, if desired. Drop by spoonfuls on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken ala king
directions: Boil chicken for 20 minutes.
Cool and then cut into cubes. Mix other ingredients.
Heat in saucepan and add chicken.
Serve over rice.

title: pizza
directions: Mix yeast with warm water.
Combine flour, salt, yeast-water mixture and oil in a large bowl.
Turn out onto floured board. Knead for 5 minutes (until dough is soft but firm).
Cover and let rise 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down and roll out.
Place a little corn meal in pie pan before placing dough in pan.
Add ingredients. Sprinkle a little oil on top of ingredients.
Bake in a 425° oven 30 to 40 minutes.

title: almond roca
directions: Generously grease two 12 x 17-inch cookie sheets.
Have rubber scrapers, spatulas or spreading knives ready for spreading.

title: cherry jubilee
directions: Mix all together.
Put in refrigerator to chill.

title: wild poke salad
directions: Trim and wash poke salad.
Cook for 1 hour in lots of water. Drain and wash.
It should be real tender.
Add other ingredients and simmer in a skillet for 20 minutes with just enough water to keep from sticking.

title: grandma plungis' poultry stuffing
directions: Crush biscuits.
Place in bowl.
Mix 1 cup milk and 1 or 2 eggs, depending on how moist you want stuffing.
Pour over crushed biscuits; set aside.
Brown sausage.
Add celery, onions and thyme.
Cook until celery and onions are halfway cooked.
Add to crushed biscuits.
Mix thoroughly and bake in greased casserole dish or stuff into chicken or turkey.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: kid's play dough
directions: Mix flour, salt and cream of tartar in heavy saucepan. Add food coloring to water. Add water and oil to flour mixture.
Stir and cook about 3 minutes until mixture pulls away from sides of pan.
Knead mixture, adding a few drops of oil.
Keep in covered containers.

title: apple dip
directions: Cream ingredients together.
Serve with apple wedges.

title: okra gumbo
directions: In Dutch oven pot at a simmer, fry your meat, onion and 3 garlic cloves.
When done, drain if needed.
Then pour in tomatoes, okra and rest of ingredients.
Simmer for about 1 hour. Pour over rice or eat with corn bread.

title: pork chop, onion, rice bake
directions: Use 13 1/2 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add rice, onion soup mix, mushrooms, pimiento and liquid.
Top with pork chops.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: mock apple  pie
directions: Bring to boil water, sugar. Put in 36 ritz crackers and lemon juice. Cook 2 minutes. Pour into pie crust and sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon. Add 2 tsp. butter. Cover with pie crust. Cut hole in middle. Bake at 425 degrees for 20 min.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine strawberries and remaining ingredients.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Cook over medium to low heat until thick.
Stir to keep from sticking.
While cooling, add about a tablespoon butter or margarine.
A couple of tablespoons of mayonnaise or salad dressing may be added.
Pour over potatoes (that have been cooked in salted water).
Celery, onions and celery seed may be added.

title: two dollar pizza
directions: Lightly flour or grease a 12-inch pizza pan.
Allow dough to defrost while being covered with a kitchen towel.
After dough has thawed (it need not rise), spread dough on pizza pan.
Combine tomato sauce, oregano, onion salt and any other favorite seasonings and spread over dough.
Sprinkle cheese and your favorite toppings over.
Bake at 400° for about 25 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Toss together peas, water chestnuts, 1 cup Chinese pea pods and red onion.
Set aside.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, pepper and salt.
Gently combine this with vegetables.
Chill.
Before serving, fold in crumbled bacon.
Garnish with extra pea pods and tomato wedges.

title: potatoes
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add drained green beans, mushroom soup and milk.
Reheat.
Place in a greased baking dish.
Layer with Velveeta cheese, French fried onions and thawed Tater Tots. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, or until Tater Tots are brown.

title: crustless spinach quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place spinach in colander to thaw. Press out all moisture.
Mix spinach with cheese, bread (torn into small pieces), eggs and nutmeg.
Transfer to 9 x 9-inch buttered dish and bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: lazy cucumber pickles
directions: Place cucumbers, onions, pepper and salt in large glass bowl. Refrigerate for 2 hours (do not drain).

title: curried fruit
directions: Drain all fruit real good on paper towels.
Place in baking dish with pineapple slices on bottom.
Stack with peach half, then apricot.
Place cherry on top.
Melt butter, brown sugar and curry.
Heat until all is melted.
Pour over fruit.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Serve warm if possible.

title: texas crab grass
directions: Melt butter in sauce pan.
Add onions and saute until translucent.
Add spinach.
Add crabmeat and cheese.
Mix thoroughly over low heat.
Transfer to chafing dish and serve with crackers or melba rounds.

title: icebox lemon dessert
directions: Cook in double boiler until thickened the egg yolks, sugar and lemon juice.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold into mixture.
Whip the cream and fold yolk mixture into cream.
Crumb the vanilla wafers and line ice cube tray or square pan.
Pour mixture over and freeze overnight.
Serves 8.

title: sweet 'n' sour beef
directions: Melt shortening in a
large skillet.
Brown beef on all sides. Add salt, tomatoes,
brown
sugar,
vinegar, onion and bay leaf. Cover skillet, lower
heat
and
let simmer about 2 hours until beef is tender.
Add
pepper
strips;
cook for 10 more minutes to blend flavors.
Serve with rice.

title: panocha frosting
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar; bring to a boil.
Cook and stir 1 minute or until slightly thick.
Cool 15 minutes.
Add hot milk and beat smooth.
Beat in confectioners sugar until spreading consistency.
Frosts two 8 or 9-inch layers.

title: hot mexican cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into a large greased pan.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: brownie candy cups
directions: You will need 30 (2-inch) foil cupcake liners.

title: raisin pie
directions: Mix and pour in uncooked pie shell. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken, then chop up.
Mix all together (except cheese). Place in baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken biscuit pie
directions: In skillet, blend soup and 1/2 cup milk.
Add next 5 ingredients. Heat to boiling, stirring frequently.
Pour into 1-quart casserole.
Combine biscuit mix and 1/3 cup milk as directed on package.
Drop by spoonfuls onto hot chicken mixture. Bake in very hot oven at 450°
for 10 to 15 minutes, or until biscuits are lightly browned.
Makes 4 servings.

title: egg casserole
directions: Cook sausage and crumble; set aside.
Scramble eggs, leaving them moist; season to taste with salt, pepper and milk.
Mix undiluted cans of soup with sausage and eggs.
Put in Pyrex dish and cover with grated cheese, if desired.
Heat at 350 degrees for 20 to 30 minutes, until bubbly.
May be kept in refrigerator overnight before cooking.

title: raspberry cream pie
directions: Mix the cream cheese and egg yolks.
In another bowl, mix the milk and lemon juice.
Add cream cheese and yolks; fold in berries.
Make meringue with egg whites and place on top.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: french fried onions
directions: Separate sliced onions.
Combine egg, flour, salt and milk. Blend well.
Dip onions into batter.
Fry in hot oil for 2 minutes or until brown.

title: finnish pancakes
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add milk and flour.
Gradually mix well. Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan (do not brown the butter).
Add batter to butter in pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with fresh or thawed frozen fruit on top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: cajun pot pie
directions: Chop the sausage and cook the bell pepper.
Mix water, cornstarch and French onion soup in a bowl.
Add this to the sausage and bell pepper.
Add seasonings, rice and shrimp.
Cook for about 5 minutes on top of stove, then pour into one pie shell. Slice 2nd pie shell in strips and place on top.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: milky way pound cake
directions: Melt butter and candy bars on low heat.
Beat shortening and sugar, add eggs one at a time.
Combine salt and flour and add to sugar mixture.
Add milk; beat well.
Then add candy mixture, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours and 10 minutes.

title: coconut sweet potato balls
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; mash and beat in melted butter and salt, brown sugar and orange juice.
Shape into 6 balls.
Roll balls in coconut moistened with 1 teaspoon melted butter.
Dip pineapple slices in melted butter and place on baking sheet.
Put a potato ball in center of each pineapple and brown in moderate oven about 15 minutes.

title: spicy egg casserole
directions: Place bread, buttered side down in pan.
Mix eggs, milk and spices.
Pour over bread.
Sprinkle chiles on top.
Top with 1 cup grated Cheddar cheese and 1 cup grated Jack cheese.
Let set overnight in the refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Other ingredients such as sausage, bacon or various veggies may be added to suit taste.

title: sausage-pasta supper
directions: In wok or large skillet, stir-fry all ingredients except sausage and cheese until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Add sausage and heat thoroughly.
Stir in cheese.
Serve over your favorite style of pasta noodles with additional Parmesan.

title: cajun corn and okra
directions: In a large saucepan, combine corn, okra, water and salt. Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Drain.
Stir in tomato, onion powder and bottled hot pepper sauce.
Heat through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sloppy joes(lots!)
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer 40 minutes to an hour.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Heat white vinegar with sugar and stir until sugar dissolves. Cool.
Mix together sauerkraut, green pepper, celery, onion and pimento.
Mix well with sugar and vinegar mixture and store in tightly covered container in refrigerator.

title: english muffins
directions: Mix and let rise.
Roll out to 1/2 inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Dip in cornmeal and put on cookie sheet and let rise again.
Cook on griddle 8 to 10 minutes on each side.

title: praline grahams
directions: Separate the crackers and place in jelly roll pan with edges touching.
Melt butter and stir in sugar and pecans.
Bring to a boil and cook 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
Spread mixture evenly over the crackers.
Bake at 300° for 12 minutes.
Remove from pan and let cool.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread fruit in bottom of 9 x 13 pan.
Spread cake mix evenly on top of fruit, then pecans.
Slice margarine in small patties and spread on top of cake.
Bake at 350°.

title: carrot cookies
directions: Mix sugar and eggs; add cooked, cooled carrots and coconut. Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
When cool, ice with thin mix of powdered sugar, butter and orange juice.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Heat onions in hot salad oil and cook until tender. Add remaining ingredients and cook until mixture is well blended. It will keep a long time in the refrigerator.

title: champagne salad
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and sugar.
Add fruit and nuts; stir.
Fold in Cool Whip and spoon into 15 cupcake liners. Freeze for 2 to 5 hours.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Beat egg and add Cool Whip.
Add sifted cake mix.
Drop about 1 tablespoonful into confectioners sugar.
Roll and place on cookie sheet.
Cook approximately 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: raspberry tartlets
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and butter.
Blend in the flour.
Chill dough.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix well.
Store in airtight container.
Use 2 heaping teaspoons to 1 cup of hot water.

title: maura's date sno-balls
directions: In a saucepan, stir 1 egg and 1 cup sugar until well blended. Add butter and dates and cook over low heat, stirring 10 minutes. Cook 15 to 30 minutes.
Add Rice Krispies and nuts.
Roll into little balls and then roll in flaked coconut.

title: all yellow sponge cake
directions: Beat egg whites until thick and lemon colored.
Add sugar gradually and continue beating with egg beater.
Measure and sift together flour, baking powder and salt and add to the mixture alternately with hot water.
Continue the beating with the egg beater.
Add any flavoring desired.
Pour in greased cake pan at 320° for 1 hour.

title: baby bear's favorite doughnuts
directions: Punch a hole in the center of each biscuit with finger.
Drop in fryer or electric skillet with 1/2-inch of oil.
Fry until brown, turn and brown other side.
Remove; drain on paper towel. Roll in cinnamon-sugar or confectioners sugar.
Makes 10 doughnuts.

title: chicken paprikash and dumplings
directions: Saute onion in shortening.
Add chicken and seasonings.
Saute 10 minutes.
Add water.
Cover and simmer until chicken is tender. Remove chicken.
Add sour cream to drippings in the pan and mix well.
Add dumplings.
Arrange chicken on top and heat through. Serve.

title: miramar pie
directions: Add the sugar slowly to the beaten egg whites with the baking powder.
Fold in the crackers and walnuts. Add the vanilla. Bake in glass pie pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool.
Spread with the whipped cream.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: sandy's scrambled egg sandwichsocorro, new mexico
directions: Toast and butter 2 slices of bread.

title: mary ann's no sugar carrot cake
directions: Mix carrots, raisins and nuts together.
Mix together in a separate bowl the flour, salt, soda, baking powder, cinnamon, allspice and nutmeg.
Beat together honey and oil.
Add this to carrot mixture.
Add dry ingredients to carrot mixture.
Separate eggs and beat yolks until frothy.
Mix into cake mixture.
Beat egg whites until very stiff.
Fold carefully into egg mixture.
Pour into a tube pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Cover bottom of an 11 x 17-inch baking pan with the sheets of crescent roll dough, patting and stretching to fit.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Combine salad dressing, sour cream, cream cheese and dry dressing mix.
Spread over cooled crust in pan.
Combine veggies, tossing to mix.
Put evenly over cheese mixture.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top. Cover with plastic wrap and push veggies into soft cheese. Refrigerate, still covered, for 3 to 4 hours.
Cut into bars. Makes 3 dozen small bars.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in cookie press and make rows of dough.
Cut into desired lengths.
Bake at 350° until golden.

title: creamed onions and carrots
directions: Cook celery in butter until tender.
Blend in soup and sour cream.
Add wine and parsley.
Cut carrots into 2-inch pieces. Add carrots and onions to soup mixture.
Heat; stir occasionally. Makes about 4 cups.

title: peanut butter puffs
directions: Beat together egg whites and salt until soft peaks form. Gradually beat in sugar.
Fold in peanut butter.
Drop by teaspoon onto dull side of aluminum foil.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: no fail divinity
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup, water and salt in a 2-quart casserole. Cook in microwave oven 19 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes. Candy thermometer should read 260°.
If not, cook 1 or 2 minutes longer.
While syrup cooks, beat egg whites very stiff in a large bowl.
Gradually pour hot syrup over egg whites and continue beating at a high speed until thick and candy start to lose its gloss.
Beating may require about 12 minutes.
Add vanilla and nuts to beaten mixture.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.

title: cukes and onions
directions: More onions or green pepper may be added.

title: baked chicken
directions: Skin chicken and dip in milk.
In plastic bag, mix all other ingredients.
Add chicken pieces and shake to coat.
Place on a slightly greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mango ice cream
directions: Cut mango.
Blend and freeze ingredients.
Serve the next day.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Stir in frozen berries until thawed. Add bananas and pineapple.
Pour 1/2 into an oblong pan. Refrigerate.
When firm, spread with sour cream.
Pour on other 1/2 jello mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar and margarine and pat onto bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix together cream cheese and 1 cup sugar.
Fold in 1 small carton of Cool Whip.
Pat gently onto cooled crust.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together; form into ball or log and roll in pecans.

title: lemon or lime mousse
directions: Whip cream and refrigerate.
In a saucepan, soften gelatin in water.
Cool.
Add lemon or lime juice.
Beat eggs and sugar together until thick and lemon colored.
Beat in gelatin mixture. Fold in half of the cream, reserving the rest.
Pour into glasses or serving dish; chill.
Garnish with remaining whipped cream when set.
Serves 6.

title: harriett's famous hamburgers
directions: Make hamburger patty.
Layer tomato slice, hamburger patty, slice of onion and slice of green pepper.
Add salt and pepper. Wrap in foil; cook on grill, 20 to 30 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding crackers last.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven until knife inserted comes out clean.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: gooey cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter or margarine and 1 egg and press in bottom of sheet cake pan.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and sugar and put on top of cake mix.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan. Melt butter and chocolate.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat lightly, just until combined (don't overbeat or brownies will rise too high and then fall).
Stir in flour and nuts.
Spread batter in pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Makes 16.

title: baked alaskan halibut
directions: Place halibut in baking dish.
Mix together remaining ingredients; pour over fish.
Bake in 350° oven until fish flakes.

title: carrot-pineapple dish
directions: Mix juice, cornstarch or flour, sugar and oleo.
Cook until thick.
Add pineapple chunks and carrots.
Heat all.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Combine warm water and yeast together in a small bowl.
Set aside.
Mix flour, salt, baking powder and sugar in a large bowl. Cut margarine into dry ingredients until fine and crumbly.
Add baking soda to buttermilk and stir well.
Pour yeast mixture and buttermilk mixture into dry ingredients and knead well.
Form the dough into a soft ball and roll out onto a floured surface (about 1/2 inch thick).
Cut biscuits and place with sides touching on a greased cookie sheet.
Let stand in a warm area 10 to 15 minutes and bake at 425° until lightly brown.

title: cherry chiffon dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: orange biscuits
directions: In a saucepan combine orange juice, 1/2 cup sugar, butter and orange peel.
Cook and stir over medium heat for 2 minutes. Divide among 12 muffin cups; set aside.
In a large bowl combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
With a fork, stir in milk until mixture forms a ball.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Heat soup.
Add gelatin mixture; cool.
Cream mayonnaise with cream cheese; add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart mold.
Chill.
Unmold on serving dish.
Serve with crackers.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then shape into a ball.
Arrange crackers around the ball.
It's great for parties.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together until tender; drain.
Melt oleo in casserole dish; pour into drained squash and onions.
Mix together egg, milk, salt and pepper.
Add to squash.
Add cracker crumbs, leaving enough to cover top.
Bake in oven about 20 minutes or until brown.
(You may add garlic salt and a little sage if you like.)

title: chicken and rice pilaf(serves 12)
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni according to directions, using chicken broth instead of water.
Mix and put in 9 x 13-inch casserole pan. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: party meatballs
directions: Combine meat, bread crumbs, eggs, onions, parsley and salt; mix thoroughly.
Shape into small (bite size) balls.
Brown in oleo.
Place in casserole.
Combine preserves and barbecue sauce; pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Keep warm. Yields 4 to 5 dozen.

title: asparagus and water chestnut salad
directions: Combine water, vinegar, sugar and salt; bring to boil and simmer until sugar is dissolved.
Sprinkle gelatin on 1/2 c. cold water to soften; stir into hot mixture until thoroughly dissolved. Chill until the consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Fold in remaining ingredients; pour into large mold and chill until set.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Mix together to make
layers. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix all together and cook at 375° in a raw 8-inch pie shell at 35 to 45 minutes.

title: rye boat dip
directions: Slice dried beef.
Mix all ingredients.
Let set for a couple of hours in refrigerator.
Pull out center of round loaf of rye bread forming a bowl with bread.
Break up the pulled out part in small pieces.
Fill "bread bowl" with dip mixture and arrange pieces around "bread bowl."
Serve.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend sugar, syrup and oleo in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Blend hot mixture slowly into beaten eggs.
Stir in pecans, vanilla and salt.
Pour into shell.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: dark rye bread(mors rugbrod)
directions: In small bowl, add sugar to warm water.
Sprinkle yeast over water.
Set aside.
In large mixing bowl, mix 2 cups white flour, dark rye flour and salt.
Add molasses, thinned with hot water. Add melted shortening and mix.
Add yeast and mix.
Gradually add remaining flour.
On a floured breadboard knead dough 8 to 10 minutes, until elastic. Put dough in greased bowl.
Let rise until double.

title: overnight lasagna
directions: Brown meat with onion and salt. Combine spaghetti sauce, water, oregano, pepper and sugar.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Put 1/2 of chicken in an 11 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put 1/2 of cooked noodles on top of chicken.
Mix the cream of chicken and cream of mushrooms soups together, then put the mixture on top of cooked noodles in dish.
Put the rest of the chicken on top of soup mixture and top with remaining noodles.
Sprinkle cheese over all. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until cheese is hot and bubbly.

title: 10 layer salad
directions: Layer in large oblong container in order listed.
Refrigerate 8 to 10 hours, covered.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve hot or cold.

title: macaroni with ham and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in salted boiling water for 12 minutes.
Drain. Arrange macaroni, ham and cheese in layers in a greased baking dish, dotting each layer of macaroni with butter.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Beat eggs, add milk, 1 teaspoon of melted butter and the lemon peel and pour over macaroni.
Place in a pot of hot water and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes oahu
directions: Use one medium sweet potato per person.
If necessary, split one large potato in half lengthwise for two people after baking. Bake at 375° until done (time depends on size of potato).
When done, remove layer of skin from top of potatoes.
Scoop out pulp and combine with crushed pineapple, salt, butter and white pepper. Reheat in the oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: sawdust pie
directions: Combine coconut, graham cracker crumbs, pecans and sugar. Mix with egg whites.
Pour mixture into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: spinach pakoras
directions: Mix all ingredients together and scoop by teaspoonfuls; fry in hot oil.

title: sweet potato drop biscuits
directions: Cream together sweet potato, yogurt, margarine and maple syrup. Set aside.
In medium bowl, mix together dry ingredients.
Add to potato mixture and beat with electric mixer.
If too hard, finish mixing by hand.

title: chicken divan
directions: Thaw broccoli in colander and pour boiling water over.
Drain and place in buttered baking dish.
Spread chicken on top. Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and poultry seasoning; spread over chicken.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Mix croutons and melted oleo and cover mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine corn and muffin mix in bowl; mix well.
Stir in margarine.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Make like biscuits.
Sift flour in a large bowl.
Make a hole in center; put all ingredients in and work with hands until you can handle dough.
Roll out on floured board about 1/4-inch thick. Sprinkle with sugar and cut out like you would a biscuit.
Will make 8 dozen.
You will have to divide dough 3 ways.
You cannot roll then all at once.
Bake about 10 minutes at 400° or until brown.
They will be crisp.

title: pink fluff
directions: Mix the milk, pineapple and berries together.
Add the nuts and Cool Whip; mix.
Let stand overnight in the refrigerator or at least 8 hours.
Stir before serving.

title: chive garlic bread
directions: In a bowl, combine the butter, parmesan cheese, chives and garlic.
Spread on one side of each slice of bread and wrap in a large piece of heavy-duty foil.
Seal in the edges.
Place on a baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes or until heated through.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: papa's turtle back cookies
directions: On medium speed of mixer, beat together all ingredients except pecans until well blended, about 2 minutes.
Stir in pecans.
Drop 5/8 cookie scoop onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350 degrees for about 12 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: angel chocolate delight
directions: Melt chocolate chips and water together.
Stir constantly. Beat the egg whites stiff; set aside.
Beat egg yolks; set aside. Stir into chocolate the beaten egg whites, then egg yolks, then Cool Whip.
Using a 13 x 9-inch pan, tear angel food cake into pieces.
Layer cake, layer of chocolate, layer of cake and layer of chocolate.
Take
the whipping cream and sweeten with sugar and vanilla.
Whip stiff and spread over last chocolate layer. Garnish with chocolate shavings.
Refrigerate for at least 12 hours.

title: orange-pineapple jello salad
directions: Bring pudding, jello and 1 1/2 cups water to a boil over medium heat.
Remove from heat and let cool completely.
After cooled, stir in Cool Whip and the drained fruit.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: rice pudding
directions: In a medium pot heat milk.
Do not let boil.
Add eggs, sugar, vanilla, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Keep stirring over medium heat.
Be sure not to let the bottom stick or burn.
Remove from heat once you feel it start to thicken.
Pour cooked rice into a 13 x 9-inch pan, then heated mixture on top.
Gently mix.
Bake in oven for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with more cinnamon or coconut and sprinkles.
Refrigerate.
Enjoy.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease muffin pans or use paper muffin cups.
Mix oil, flour and sugar together well.
Add eggs, milk, baking powder and salt to mixture and stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in blueberries.
Spoon into muffin cups and bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat together shortening, eggs, brown sugar, white sugar and vanilla.
Add and beat well the flour, baking soda, and Cream of Wheat.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Lightly grease your cookie sheet.
(Cool slightly before removing from cookie sheet.)

title: chocolate nut wafers
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg and vanilla together.
Add chocolate.
Sift together flour and salt.
Mix in nuts.
Stir into liquid mixture.
Mix to form dough.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 300° for a little over an hour.

title: table syrup
directions: Boil for 5 minutes, then add maple flavoring.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Brown meat with egg, onion, rice, spices and 1/2 c. stewed tomatoes. Cook until done.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together (you may add food coloring); roll in nut meats or parsley.
Chill.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well; shape into ball.
Roll in pecans and chill.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: salmon puff
directions: Combine eggs, milk and soup.
Blend in remaining ingredients and place in buttered casserole dish.
Bake for 45 minutes in moderately hot oven.

title: taco dip
directions: Combine softened cream cheese with taco sauce using a mixer in a large mixing bowl.
Spread mixture in a pan.
Sprinkle on diced tomato and onion.
Spread top with shredded cheese.
Serve with taco chips.

title: pound cake with apples
directions: Butter and sprinkle with bread crumbs a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Peel and core apples, cut into quarters and make several lengthwise incisions into back of each quarter.
Sprinkle the sugar on top of the apples.
Set aside.

title: pennsylvania chocolate dutch cake
directions: Mix oil, milk, coffee, vanilla and eggs in bowl.
In another bowl, mix dry ingredients and add gradually to liquids.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until center springs back when touched.

title: honey muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place paper liner in muffin pans.
In large bowl, mix flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In medium bowl, beat egg.
Stir in milk, oil, honey and orange peel. Make a well in flour mixture; pour egg mixture in.
Stir together with fork only until flour is moistened (batter will be lumpy). Fill muffin cups 2/3 full; put a teaspoon of orange marmalade onto batter in each cup.
Bake for 20 minutes, or until golden brown. Remove; cool on cooling rack.

title: lobster bisque
directions: In a large steam kettle, bring milk and half and half to 160°. Add lobster base, paprika, salt, white pepper and sherry.
Stir well.
Add roux and stir well.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes at 180°. Drain through china cap and add lobster meat (steamed 2 minutes) at the end.
Yields 5 gallons.

title: touch of grace biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Spray an 8-inch round cake pan with cooking spray.

In medium bowl, mix the self-rising flour, cake flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda until well blended. Cut in shortening with a pastry blender or your fingertips until lumps are no larger than peas.
Stir in cream and buttermilk and let stand 2 to 3 minutes.
Dough should be very wet.
If not, add a little more cream to achieve a sloppy consistency.

title: tangy lemonade pie(diabetic)
directions: Prepare gelatin according to package directions.
Refrigerate until almost set.
Transfer to blender or food processor.
Add the cream cheese and lemonade mix; cover and process until smooth. Pour into the crust.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with whipped topping.
Yields:
6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into a 9 x 12 x 2-inch casserole dish and top with 2 cups Pepperidge Farm cornbread stuffing mix, tossed with 1/2 cup melted light margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until lightly brown.

title: teriyaki yakitori
directions: Prepare marinade by mixing all ingredients except steak.
Trim meat, slice thinly and marinate 4 to 6 hours.
Thread on skewers. Barbecue 12 to 15 minutes, turning frequently.
Do not overcook.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake in a 300° oven for 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: pepperoni and broccoli pasta
directions: In large skillet, cook garlic in the oil over low heat until tender.
Do not brown.
Mash softened garlic to release flavor. Add pepperoni and cook until slightly browned.
Add well drained broccoli and heat until flavors are blended.
Mix in hot, cooked and well drained macaroni.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Bring to just below boiling point and pour over first mixture. Keep in a container that doesn't absorb odors.
This will keep for weeks and will stay crisp.
Especially good for Thanksgiving and Christmas.

title: cooked custard eggnog
directions: Heat milk in a large saucepan (do not boil).
Beat eggs and salt in large bowl; gradually add sugar, mixing well.
Gradually stir about 1/4 of hot milk into egg mixture; add remaining hot milk, stirring constantly.
Cook over medium-low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and reaches 160°.
Stir in 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg and vanilla.
Set saucepan in larger pan of ice for 10 minutes to rapidly cool mixture.
Cover and refrigerate up to 48 hours.

title: good-looking and easy pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt margarine in large iron skillet.
Put in brown sugar. When mixture is mixed well together and looks like sauce, remove from heat.
Arrange pineapple rings, cherries and nuts in pattern as desired.
Place nuts around side of skillet as far up as you can put them.
Enjoy creating new and different patterns.
Prepare cake mix as directed except for amount of water.
Use pineapple juice you saved and add it to it to make the water amount required for cake mix.
Pour cake mix evenly over pattern you have created. Nut lovers you may add nuts to the cake mix or sprinkle nuts on top of mix, if desired.
Bake at 350° until tip is browned and springs back (about 35 minutes).
Remove from oven and let stand 10 minutes.
Take sharp knife and loosen cake from side of skillet.
Turn over on favorite cake dish or large plate.
Remove skillet.
There it is, good-looking and easy pineapple upside-down cake.
May use 13 x 9-inch pan, if skillet is not available.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Blend soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Stir in chicken (if using barbecue chicken, skin and debone) and vegetables.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Mix melted oleo and cornflake crumbs.
Spread over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ham barbecue
directions: Cook all ingredients together, 20 to 30 minutes.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 15-inch pan.
Pour berries over margarine.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar over berries.
Mix flour, baking powder, 1 1/4 cups sugar, milk and salt together and pour over berries.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Boil and debone chicken; tear into bite size pieces.
Layer 1/2 chicken in 13 x 9-inch pan; mix soups and cream cheese together.
Layer 1/2 on top of chicken.
Cook stuffing. Layer 1/2 on chicken.
Cook egg noodles and drain. Layer 1/2 on chicken mixture.
And then repeat layers.
Bake until heated through.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Place one piece of
chicken,
bone
side up, between two pieces of clear plastic wrap
and,
working
from the center to the
edge, pound meat
lightly
to
about
1/4-inch
thickness. (Pounding the meat to an even thickness helps it to cook faster and more evenly.) Repeat process with each piece.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix together all ingredients but add ginger ale last.
Serves 25.

title: green or orange punch
directions: Put ice cream or sherbet in a large bowl; let soften.
Mix with a potato masher.
Add juices and ginger ale. Mix and serve.

title: chocolate sheet cake brownies
directions: Mix flour, sugar and baking soda together; set aside.
Mix together in a saucepan the butter, cocoa and water; bring to a boil.
Pour this mixture over dry ingredients; mix well.
Add buttermilk, vanilla, slightly beaten eggs, chopped walnuts and, if desired, Reese's peanut butter chips.
Mix altogether well.
Pour into greased flat 11 x 16-inch cookie sheet or 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Frost while cake is hot.

title: tangy potato salad with bacon
directions: In a large bowl, mix the sour cream, mayonnaise, green onions, pickle juice, red pepper, salt and mustard.
Add the potatoes, bacon and egg and mix well.
Refrigerate, tightly covered, for at least 1 hour.
Will keep for up to 2 days.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Beat together the egg, sugar and oil. Add flour mixture, raisins and nuts.
Stir only until moistened. Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 25 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: cheese spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti in salty water; drain and rinse.

title: spinach salad
directions: Tear spinach; throw away stems.
Mix with remaining ingredients.

title: picnic bean bake
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; crumble and set aside.
Cook beef until browned; drain off fat.
Combine beef, bacon and rest of ingredients.
Pour into a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: hal's dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish pour the pineapple, spreading it out a little.
Pour in the cherry pie filling.
Don't stir. Sprinkle the cake mix over the filling.
Melt the margarine and sprinkle it over the cake mix.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans. Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: no-baking cookies
directions: Bring milk, oleo, sugar and cocoa to hard boil.
Remove from heat and add oats, vanilla and nuts.
Beat until thick and drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Let cool until in candy form.

title: favorite rhubarb crisp
directions: Beat egg and stir in granulated sugar and 2 Tbsp. flour.
Add rhubarb and blend.
Spoon into buttered 8 inch baking dish. Combine margarine, brown sugar and 2/3 c. flour and cut to crumbs. Sprinkle over rhubarb.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Note: Doubles nicely.

title: banana cream pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together except wafers.
Layer bottom of bowl with wafers.
Pour half of mixture over.
Layer with wafers and pour remaining mixture over.
Top with remaining wafers.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Save some nuts for garnish.
Melt oleo in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Add flour, nuts and sugar.
Mix well.
