Pat firmly and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: orange-apple muffins
directions: Combine orange
juice and bran.
Add egg, oil and brown sugar; mix
well.
Mix
remaining
dry
ingredients in another bowl.
Add the
dry ingredients to the moist ingredients; mix just until moistened.
Stir
in apple bits.
Fill foil baking cups 2/3 full. Bake
in
a
oven
for about 15 minutes. Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: cherry-apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place apples in a greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Spread cherry pie filling over apples.
Combine flour, cinnamon, sugar and cereal.
Add butter, stirring until well mixed.
Sprinkle mixture over cherry and
apple layer.
Bake in preheated oven about 25 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with ice cream of plain cream.

title: no-bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Blend the sugar and cocoa in a large pan.
Add the milk and butter and heat on moderate heat until it boils, stirring constantly.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and stir.
Add the oatmeal and mix well.
Drop by tablespoon on wax paper.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Saute sausage; drain and crumble.
Add onions and green pepper and cook until tender.
Remove from heat and add sauteed mushrooms.
Add bread crumbs and eggs and mix.
Place heaping teaspoon of sausage mixture in each mushroom cap.
Place on cookie sheet.
With pastry brush, spread on melted butter.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and cheese is melted (10 to 15 minutes).
Serve at once.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add sugar.
Mix all together; store in closed bowl in refrigerator.
Knead dough before making biscuits.
Do not let rise before baking.
Bake at 425° until done.
Use as needed.

title: life's recipe
directions: Mix these thoroughly.
Add tears of joy, sorrow and sympathy for others.
Flavor with little gifts of love.
Fold in 4 cups of meditation and faith to lighten other ingredients and raise the texture to great heights of meaningful living.
Pour all this into daily life and bake well with the heat of human kindness.
Serve with a smile.

title: chicken and vegetable a la grands!
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Prepare and bake biscuits according to package directions.*

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and onion in water until done; don't overcook. Drain broccoli. Add rest of the ingredients. Place in 9 x 13 pan. Top with crushed crackers. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In skillet, brown meat with bell pepper and onion; pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients except buns.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve on buns. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: rice tomato soup
directions: Fry bacon crisp; saute onions.
Put tomatoes, chicken broth and onions in a large pan and bring to a boil.
Add rice and crumbled bacon and boil on lower heat until rice is cooked.

title: my steak salad
directions: Heat Canola oil to very hot in deep skillet or wok.
Quickly add steak and saute until tender, salt and peppering to taste. Drain and let cool a little.
Toss vegetables and steak in large bowl and use salad dressing of your choice.
(I use Zesty Italian; lite is fine.) Serve in bowls with hot rolls or Italian bread sticks.
Complete meal with dessert.
Serves 4.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Place pineapple in saucepan.
Mix together sugar and cornstarch, add to pineapple.
Bring to boil over medium heat and cook, stirring, 2 minutes or until thick and clear.
Remove from heat, add butter and lemon juice.
Line pie pan with pastry, pour in filling, adjust top crust or make lattice strips.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken fricassee
directions: Flour, salt and pepper chicken.
Brown chicken in small amount of Crisco.
As each piece gets brown, take out of skillet and cool.
Remove all meat from bones.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Blend flour, Crisco, baking powder and salt with pastry blender until it resembles coarse meal.
Add milk and stir.
Roll out on floured surface in rectangle form.
Melt 1 stick butter in a 13 x 9-inch dish; set aside.
Boil sugar and water until melted.
Place sliced fresh peaches on crust and roll as if jelly roll.
Slice into 16 pieces and place in dish with melted butter. Pour water and sugar mixture over sliced pieces.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Use with any fresh fruit.

title: country baked beans
directions: Fry bacon crisp. Drain on towel and crumble. Fry diced onions in drippings from bacon. Put beans in greased casserole. Stir in onion, drippings and bacon. Add brown sugar, mustard and catsup. Mix well and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 minutes until brown and bubbly.

title: eggplant with mozzarella
directions: Lightly sprinkle the eggplant slices with salt on both sides. Place them between two plates and top with a weight.
Let eggplant drain for about an hour.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender, process until smooth.

title: geometric salad
directions: Put jello in large bowl.
Add 1 cup boiling water.
Stir until jello dissolves.
Add the strawberries until thawed out, then add the other fruits.
Mix together.
Pour 1/2 mixture into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Put in refrigerator until jello sets.
Mix sour cream and yogurt together.
Spread over top of jello.
Add rest of jello.
Put in refrigerator until firm.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: grandma white's rhubarb custard pie
directions: Cream together egg yolks with next 3 ingredients. Pour over rhubarb in pastry shell and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Make meringue of egg whites, 2 tablespoons sugar and vanilla.
Top pie and bake at 425° until lightly browned.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Put in refrigerator until set and serve.

title: chili lentils
directions: Bring water to boil and add lentils, cover and simmer 30 minutes or until tender and drain.
Cook ground chuck, onion and garlic until browned.
Combine meat mixture, lentils, tomatoes, chili powder, oregano and salt in Dutch oven and cook over high heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut or pecan patties
directions: Cook sugar, syrup, milk and peanuts together until it forms hard (firm) ball when dropped in cold water.
Take off stove and add 1/2 stick oleo and vanilla.
Let set about 15 to 20 minutes. Stir once in awhile.
Then beat until it forms mounds when dropped by spoon on buttered foil.
I put my peanuts in oven and roast a little while, but you don't have to.

title: old fashioned pumpkin pie
directions: Line 2 (8-inch) pie pans with unbaked pastry.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine ingredients in order given.
Bake for 10 minutes. Reduce heat quickly and bake 30 minutes at 350° or until knife comes out clean inserted in center.

title: fancy fruit and dip
directions: To make the fruit dip:
Mix in a bowl the sour cream, frozen orange juice, milk (use orange juice container to measure milk amount) and vanilla pudding mix.
Blend until firm and smooth.

title: antipasto salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Rinse with cold water to cool quickly; drain well.
In small bowl, whisk together oil, vinegar, sugar and seasonings.
In large bowl, combine pasta, dressing and remaining ingredients.
Cover; refrigerate for several hours for best flavor.
Makes 12 servings.

title: dirt pie
directions: Crumble cookies in a large bowl.
Mix pudding according to directions.
Mix pudding, cream cheese and cookies together. Place in a glass bowl and chill.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Remove outside leaves.
Wash cabbage.
Cut into wedges, coarsely shred cabbage with knife and throw away core.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat until hot.
Add cabbage, garlic, red pepper and sugar.
Stir continuously for 2 minutes; add onion. Stir until vegetables are very tender.

title: summer's end stew
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown meat in oil over medium heat.
Add tomatoes, tomato juice or water, onions, garlic, pepper and salt. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour.
Add potatoes, carrots, corn, green beans, peas and celery.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add squash; simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until meat and vegetables are tender.
Stir in parsley and sugar.

title: chocolate oil cake
directions: *To make sour milk, add 1/4 c. vinegar to milk.
Mix all ingredients together, except add water last, and pour into mixture slowly.
Beat well each time.
Add vanilla last.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Do not open oven door first 20 minutes.

title: chocolate heaven
directions: Mix butter, flour and chopped nuts.
Press in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° until slightly browned.

title: black cherry jello salad
directions: Drain the fruit cocktail about 30 minutes. Add the sugar and jello; mix, then let chill until firm.

title: pecan delight pie
directions: Beat egg whites, baking powder and salt until thick. Gradually add sugar.
Beat until it holds peaks.
Fold in cracker crumbs and pecans.
Pour into greased pie pan and bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cover top with whipped cream before serving.

title: smothered corn(serves 6)
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, cook onion and green pepper until tender (about 5 minutes). Stir in corn, tomato, salt and peppers. Reduce heat to low; cover and cook until corn is tender (about 5 minutes). Season to taste.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all fruit.
Stir in peach pie filling, blend well.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Put a little cinnamon, sugar and butter inside each apple. Mix together flour, shortening, Milnot and dash of salt.
Roll out and cut into 12 pieces of dough.
Wrap around apples and place in dish.
In bowl, mix 2 cups sugar, 3 cups hot water, 1 1/2 sticks butter, 1/2 bottle liquid cinnamon and red food coloring.
Pour over apples and bake at 350° until apples are soft.

title: electric skillet supper
directions: Pat about 3/4 ground beef in bottom of skillet; add cut up vegetables in layers.
Crumble remainder of ground beef on top of the vegetables.
Spread soup over this mixture and place the slices of cheese on top.
Start on medium high heat in electric skillet (325°).
After mixture starts steaming, turn down on low (close steam vents) and cook about 20 minutes longer or until vegetables are done.

title: make night before oklahoma chocolate delight
directions: Use pastry cutter to mix the flour and margarine until crumbly.
Add the pecans and dump into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Pat out mixture on bottom of pan and bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes.

title: cornbread
directions: Put oil in iron skillet in hot oven (425° to 450°) to melt. Do not burn.
Mix dry ingredients well. Add milk and egg.
Mix well. Add hot oil.
Mix.
Flour skillet and pour in bread mixture. Bake until brown, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cocoa
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together in saucepan; bring to boil.
Add the milk and vanilla; heat again until hot.
Add marshmallows when served.

title: mexican pronto
directions: Brown beef, shortening and onion together.
Drain.
Mix next 5 ingredients with beef mixture.
Make layers of beef mixture, chips and cheese in a large baking dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: penuche fudge
directions: Combine butter, sugars, salt and sour cream in saucepan. Simmer until sugar is melted, then cover and cook for 5 minutes over medium heat.
Remove cover and cook to soft ball stage (234° to 240° on candy thermometer).
Do not stir.
Set pan in cold water until mixture cools to lukewarm.
Stir in nuts and vanilla. Spread in greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Cool and cut into pieces.

title: mom's lemon pie
directions: Mix whipped topping, lemonade, condensed milk and lemon juice. Pour into pie crusts.
Freeze for 3 hours.
Take out of freezer 15 minutes before serving.

title: microwave cinnamon twists
directions: Roll each biscuit into a 9-inch rope.
Melt butter for 45 seconds.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Dip each rope into cinnamon-sugar mixture and twist.
Place in a circle on a glass plate.
Microwave on High 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.

title: mexican dorito casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion, and green pepper.
Drain.
Mix soups, sauce, milk, and cheese in pan.
Add meat and chips.
Blend together.
Bake in oven at 350°F for about 20 - 30 min.

title: blueberry upside down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter a 1 quart, 5 1/2 inch diameter souffle dish.
Pour 2 Tbsp. melted butter into the souffle dish. Sprinkle 3 Tbsp. brown sugar over butter.
Scatter 1 c. blueberries over sugar.
Set aside.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage. Mix all ingredients together. Put into 11 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle 1 cup shredded Cheddar cheese over the top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: suki rice
directions: Brown sausage in soy sauce.
Add onion, potatoes, carrots and seasonings.
Cook until tender.
Stir in rice and add a little more soy sauce.

title: "no-fail" sausage balls
directions: Preparation time: 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer chicken, 1/2 of dressing and cream of celery/mushroom soup in a medium sized, greased casserole dish.
Repeat layers using cream of chicken soup.
Pour 1 soup can of water over tops and sides of casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until bubbly.
This can be prepared ahead of time and baked just before serving.

title: mother's brisket
directions: Sprinkle brisket that has had the fat trimmed off with garlic powder, celery and onion salt. Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over meat. Cover with Saran Wrap and let it marinate overnight in a glass dish. Cook covered with foil at 300° for 3 1/2 hours. Remove foil and cook without cover for 30 more minutes. Enjoy.

title: easy chocolate chip cheesecake pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
With mixer, beat cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in milk until smooth.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Toss morsels with flour; stir into cheese mixture.
Pour into Ready-Crust graham cracker pie crust.
Bake 35 minutes or until center springs back when lightly touched.
Cool and top with glaze.
Serve chilled.

title: persimmon-raisin cookies
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add egg and beat well.
Combine flour, spices and salt; add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Combine persimmon pulp and soda; stir well (it will thicken) and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop by level tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until done.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: pizza style baked spaghetti
directions: Break spaghetti into thirds and cook; drain.
Beat eggs and milk together in a large bowl.
Add spaghetti; toss to mix.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer the next 4 ingredients over spaghetti in order listed.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and oregano. Top with pepperoni and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: mexican fiesta casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add taco seasoning, picante sauce, rice, corn and kidney beans; simmer.
Stir in cheese before serving.
Serve on a bed of lettuce.
It is very good with taco chips.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine.
Mix with sugar, then add eggs, one at a time, and mix (add next egg, mix, etc.).
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill batter for 2 hours.
Drop into confectioners sugar; roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: heavenly rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a covered casserole dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dolly parton's cowboy pork and beans
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and pepper in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: easy tuna casserole
directions: Layer ingredients:
potatoes, onions and tuna.
Repeat layers. Spread soup over top, then pour milk over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy dill pickles
directions: Pack cucumbers in jars.
Heat water, salt and vinegar to boiling.
Add 1 teaspoon dill seed, 1 teaspoon of mustard seed and 1 clove garlic to each jar of cucumbers.
Pour boiling mixture over cucumbers and spices in jars to within 1/2 inch of top.
Add seals and screw on lids tight.
Place in boiling water bath for 15 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cut all of the vegetables into chunks (no tiny pieces).
Toss with margarine, garlic salt to taste and pepper.
Combine everything in a 2 to 3-quart casserole dish.
Cover and cook at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Uncover and cook for an additional 1/2 hour (makes its own juices).
Serve immediately.
Goes well with any meat.

title: dutch baby(puffy dessert or breakfast pancake)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Unwrap butter and put in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Put pan in oven until butter melts.
Meanwhile, beat the eggs.
Then add milk and flour.
Stir until just blended. Batter should be lumpy.
Pour batter into pan with butter and return to oven.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until puffed and golden. Serve immediately.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner according to directions on package. Put in skillet a teaspoon oleo and cook until tender the onion, pimento and pepper. Add tuna, mushroom soup and grated cheese. Mix together with dinner and bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients until soft ball stage and add last 3 ingredients at once.
Remove from fire and drop by spoon on wax paper.

title: daddy's oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt and soda together.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Soak raisins in warm water for 10 minutes; drain well.
Add raisins, uncooked oatmeal and coconut. Beat eggs and milk together.
Add to mixture.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Drop heaping teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375 °. Makes 72 cookies.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Add to other ingredients in boiler.
Boil for a few minutes.

title: fruit pizza(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Cut cookie dough in 1/8-inch slices.
Line a 14-inch pizza pan with foil.
Arrange cookie slices, slightly overlapping.
Bake 12 minutes at 375°.
Cool completely.
Blend cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over crust.
Arrange fruit in circles over cheese layer.
Glaze fruit that will discolor, lemon juice and sugar. Chill.
Cut with pizza cutter to serve.
Pretty on a buffet.

title: chili con queso
directions: In large skillet, brown meat.
Add green onion; cook over low heat until tender but not brown.
Add tomato sauce, chili peppers, Worcestershire and cheese.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until all cheese melts.
Stir in garlic powder.
Serve in chafing dish over a low heat source with corn chips.
Makes 1-quart sauce.

title: baked fish with salsa
directions: Cut fillets into serving size portions.
Rub with 2 tablespoons olive oil and sprinkle lightly with salt and ground pepper.
Place fish in one layer in baking dish.
Cover with foil and bake in 425° oven about 20 minutes or until cooked through. Remove from oven and spread thin layer of salsa over top.
Return to oven for 3 to 5 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Add 1/3 cup of lemon juice and toss.
Pour filling into the graham cracker crusts and chill thoroughly before serving.

title: dream pie
directions: Mix well the Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Add Cool Whip; stir well.
Add cherry pie filling.
Pour into graham cracker crusts.
Makes 2 pies.

title: gara's cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream sugars and butter. Add eggs and flour mixture.
Add vanilla, nuts and candied cherries.
Spoon out cookies in 1 1/2-inch balls.
Bake at 400° until slightly browned on edges.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Bake in preheated oven at 350° in well-greased sheet pan for 25 minutes.

title: mexican taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger with taco mix.
Put hamburger on bottom of a 6 x 8-inch pan.
Spread refried beans on top of hamburger.
Next, spread salsa on top of refried beans and top off with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Take out of oven and let set for about 5 minutes, then spread sour cream on top.
Dip tortilla chips and enjoy.

title: deviled steak
directions: For sauce, mix catsup, water, Worcestershire, dry mustard and pepper.
Grill meat for 6 minutes.
Brush with sauce.
Turn and grill until done.
Brush frequently with sauce.
Makes 4 servings; 195 calories each.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Divide into pans and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: microwave creamy cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage in 2-quart microproof casserole. Add water. Cook, covered, on High 7 to 9 minutes or until done. Stir once during cooking time.
Add remaining ingredients except paprika. Cook covered on High (max power) 1 minute. Stir carefully to mix cheese with cabbage. Garnish with paprika.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain beets, reserve the liquid.
Cut beets into bite-sized pieces.
In a medium saucepan, mix the sugar, cornstarch, cloves, vinegar and beet juice.
Bring to a boil, boiling for 1 minute. Add beets and oleo or butter, heat on medium until hot.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Cream the shortening; add sugar, beaten eggs, cream, fruit, nuts and coconut.
Beat well.
Add the dry ingredients. Shape in balls and press down on greased cookie sheet or spread and cut in squares.
Bake in 375° oven 10 to 12 minutes.

title: lentil burgers
directions: Combine the ingredients in a bowl.
Mix all ingredients together, using just enough tomato juice to hold mixture in shape when pattied.
Fry like hamburgers in a small amount of hot oil. Serves 6.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Place all ingredients into large oven-proof casserole dish and mix well.
Bake at 250 degrees for 5 hours.
Yield: 6-8 servings.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Add taco seasoning and water. Simmer 15 minutes. Add tomatoes, enchilada sauce and Colby cheese. Simmer for 20 minutes. Fill each tortilla with 1 tablespoon of sauce and fold. Arrange in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Pour remaining sauce over all. Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with shredded lettuce, sour cream, sliced black olives and nacho chips, by guests as they desire.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain well. Crush Ritz crackers.
Spread 1/2 of the cracker crumbs in a shallow baking dish.
Heat cheese, soup, butter and milk in a saucepan until cheese melts.
Pour broccoli into dish on top of cracker crumbs.
Put melted cheese mixture over broccoli; top with the remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, or until cracker crumbs brown slightly.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Peel shrimp and devein.
Place shrimp and butter in a covered dish.
Cook on High in the microwave for 5 minutes.
Combine seasoning, water, cornstarch, pepper, lemon juice and parsley. Mix well.
Pour over shrimp and stir.
Cook, covered, 5 minutes. Uncover and cook 5 more minutes.
Serve on vermicelli or spaghetti.

title: mothers delight
directions: Butter casserole dish and put in rice (not cooked).
Layer with chicken or pork chops (raw) on rice.
Sprinkle pork chops or chicken with dry onion soup mix.

title: pumpkin custard pie
directions: Cream eggs, milk and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well until well blended.
Pour into a 9-inch deep pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice and set aside.
Meanwhile, in mixing bowl, add all other ingredients together including beaten eggs, then stir into cooked rice.
Pour into baking dish and bake, stirring once, then let brown slightly.
Serve warm or cold.

title: cherry glazed chicken
directions: Combine flour, thyme, pepper and salt.
Dip chicken pieces in milk, then in flour mixture.
Coat evenly with flour.

title: two potato soup
directions: Trim leek, cutting off all but 1 inch or so of green.
Rinse leek under running water to remove all sand between leaves, then chop finely.
In 2 1/2 quart microwave-safe bowl, melt butter.
Add leek and cover with vented plastic.
Microwave on High for 3 to 5 minutes until leek is tender.
Stir in broth, both potatoes, pepper and nutmeg.
Cover with vented plastic and microwave on High 15 to 18 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Transfer to blender. Process until smooth.
Return to bowl and stir in milk.
Cover and microwave on High 1 to 3 minutes.
Stir once until heated.
Can be doubled and done on stove.
Freezes great!!

title: christmas scent
directions: Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer, adding water to keep from drying up.
May keep refrigerated in tightly covered jar for several days.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat after each.
Add soda, buttermilk, vanilla and flour, then add orange slices, dates, coconut and pecans.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours in greased and floured tube pan.
You may add grated orange rind if desired.

title: cowboy biscuits
directions: Mix, then turn and knead on floured board.
Put in a greased bowl.
Let rise until doubled.
Work it down and make rolls; let rise again.

title: logan's favorite nine layer dip
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet. Combine the 6 following ingredients in skillet with hamburger. Simmer 5 minutes.
Keep warm.

title: raisin molasses honeys with cornflakes
directions: Rinse raisins in hot water; drain and dry on a towel.
Cream butter or substitute.
Add honey and molasses; beat well.
Add beaten egg yolks and flavoring.
Stir to blend.
Add flour sifted with baking powder and salt; beat.
Stir in raisins and cornflakes, alternately with stiffly beaten egg whites.
Drop by small spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet, about 2-inches apart. Flatten slightly.
Bake in a moderate oven (375°) for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 1/2 to 5 dozen medium-sized cookies.

title: raisin bread pudding
directions: Tear bread into small pieces and put into 2-quart baking dish. In blender, mix eggs, milk, water, sugar and vanilla.
Pour over bread.
Set pudding pan in a larger pan of water.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until knife inserted in pudding comes out clean.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add milk and vanilla.
Melt margarine in 8 x 8-inch baking dish in oven.
Pour batter into dish.
Cover with fruit.
Bake at 375° until brown. Just before completely brown, dot with margarine and sprinkle with sugar.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
In a bowl stir milk into soup; add chicken, 1/2 cup of the cheese, mushrooms and macaroni.
Mix well.
Place mixture in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 50 minutes.
Uncover and stir; top with remaining cheese and bake until cheese melts.

title: glycerin soap bubbles
directions: Put mixture in small jar.
Add straws to blow.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Heat chicken
broth
to
a
boil.
Lower
heat	and add chopped onions, bay
leaf and Parmesan cheese to make a paste. Add herbs,
mustard
and
pepper.
Butter a baking dish.
Coat chicken with
the cheese paste generously.	Bake in 375° oven, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Baste occasionally.
Add water, if necessary.

title: four bean casserole
directions: Cook together the bacon, onions, brown sugar and mustard. Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add all beans.
Bake in a large casserole dish for 2 hours at 325°.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: lasagne ludy
directions: Note:
Ricotta cheese may be used, but sparingly.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk, lemon juice and sour cream with mixer. Pour into crust. Spoon apples on top. Sprinkle nuts and cinnamon on top of apples. Bake at 400° for 18 minutes. Don't overbake.

title: easy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix and drop by teaspoons onto a buttered cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: cherry pudding delight
directions: Melt oleo in deep Pyrex dish. Mix together sugar, self-rising flour and milk to make a thin batter. Add batter to center of oleo. Don't stir! Add cherry pie filling on top of batter. Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until brown. Crust will cook to the top.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: dorset apple cake
directions: Butter and flour 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 3/4-inch loaf pan.
Line bottom of dish with waxed paper.
Butter and flour paper.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, sugar and baking powder into large bowl with a pastry blender or knives; cut in butter until mixture resembles fine meal.
Toss chopped apple in flour mixture; set aside.
In small bowl, whisk together egg and milk until blended. Stir into apple mixture until mixed.
(Batter will be stiff.) Spread batter evenly in pan.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes until knife comes out clean.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add vegetables, garlic, pepperoni and 1 jar Ragu.
Simmer 10 to 20 minutes.
Add Ricotta and 1 1/2 to 2 cups Mozzarella.
Stir well and cool.
Stuff cooked macaroni shells with meat mixture.
Pour 1/4 jar Ragu in bottom of baking dish.
Place stuffed shells open side down.
Top with remaining sauce and shredded Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Freezes well.

title: fig jam
directions: Mash figs and mix with sugar and Jell-O.
Bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Cool and put into jars.

title: beautiful cherry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Cool until slightly jelled. Add sour cream and cherry pie filling.
Pour into mold and refrigerate.

title: rum cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Mix cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, water, rum and oil until smooth.
Pour into prepared pan and bake for 1 hour.

title: spice cut-up cookies
directions: Boil together 5 minutes the first 5 ingredients.
When cool, add the remaining ingredients (sifted together).
Cool before mixing; bake on cookie sheet or dripping pan at 350° until done. Glaze when cool.

title: green angel cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package, folding dry Jell-O into 1/3 of the batter.
Alternately spoon batters into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Zigzag spatula through batters.
Bake on lowest rack at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes until cake springs back when lightly pressed.
Turn pan upside down over funnel or bottle to cool completely.
Remove from pan. Frost and garnish with lime slices (if desired).
Keep chilled.

title: peppermint patties
directions: Mix cream cheese, butter and sugar. Add flavoring. Pat into patties and dip in chocolate coating. Let cool.

title: asparagus romanoff
directions: In a saucepan over low heat, combine soup, Worcestershire sauce and sour cream.
Stir constantly and heat to just below boiling.

title: pasta bean soup
directions: Cook and stir onion, garlic and meat in oil over medium heat about 5 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes with liquid, water, oregano, thyme and pepper.
Break up tomatoes with fork.
Heat to boiling. Stir in macaroni and potatoes.
Reduce heat.
Cook uncovered until macaroni is tender, about 10 minutes.
Stir in beans and zucchini. Cook until zucchini is crisp-tender, about 3 minutes.
You can sprinkle servings with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: scotcharoo's
directions: Melt peanut butter and butterscotch morsels in microwave; stir every 30 seconds. Takes 1 to 1 1/2 minutes. Stir until blended. Add chow mein noodles. Add/stir until well coated. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper-lined cookie sheet. Top with halved cherries (but not necessary). Chill until set! YUMMY.

title: pineapple ham balls
directions: In a bowl, combine ham, pork, bread crumbs, eggs and pepper and mix well.
Chill, then form into 10 balls; set aside.
Drain pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup of juice.
Place juice in a saucepan with sugar, vinegar and dry mustard; cook and stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Arrange pineapple slices in the bottom of an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place ham ball on each pineapple slice.
Pour sugar mixture over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until ham balls are well done.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: beef casserole
directions: Mix all of the ingredients in a 2-quart Corning dish.
Cover and bake at 325° for 3 hours.

title: peanut butter brownie cups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix brownie mix according to package directions.
Fill paper lined muffin cups 2/3 full.
Place 1 candy in center of brownie batter; press down until batter meets the top edge of the candy.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: garlic oil
directions: Place the garlic and corn oil in jar, close cover, let stand 1 to 2 weeks, then strain.
Use for salad dressings, marinades, sauces or stir-frying.

title: fluffy flapjacks
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, salt and sugar and mix.
Add egg and buttermilk to dry ingredients.
Fry on griddle until brown on both sides.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients in large bowl; set aside. Place margarine, shortening and water in saucepan; bring to a boil. Pour this over dry ingredients and mix. Add soda to buttermilk; add vanilla and eggs, then mix. Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until cake is done.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt together cheese and margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread in large pan and chill.

title: mandarin chicken salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Add remaining ingredients to first mixture just prior to serving.
Serve on bed of lettuce.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries, sugar and pineapple in a pan and cook until cranberries pop.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Add the rest of ingredients and mix together.

title: mystery casserole
directions: Cook chicken and then cut into bite size pieces.
Add to casserole dish. Add the mushroom soup and sour cream to casserole dish and mix. After preparing dressing, add to top of the casserole. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Curry powder can be added to taste to the chicken mixture.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream oleo, sugar, eggs, applesauce and milk.
Add flour, salt, soda, cloves, cinnamon, allspice and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Mixture will be thick.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into 3 (9-inch) round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool completely.

title: coney sauce
directions: Brown ground beef slowly, thoroughly breaking with fork until fine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer uncovered 10 minutes. Makes sauce for 10 coneys.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into a large, greased casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: chicken mozzarella
directions: Preparation:
15 to 20 minutes.
Cooking Time: 20 to 25 minutes.
Temperature: 350°.

title: chewy butter n' nut clusters
directions: In large bowl, stir together cereal and nuts; set aside.
In 2-quart saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.
Stir in sugar and syrup.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until mixture comes to a full boil.
Continue cooking until mixture reaches soft ball stage (candy thermometer will read 238°).
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Toss candy mixture with cereal and nuts.
Spread evenly onto buttered cookie sheet.
Cool completely; break into clusters.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Mix oleo, sugars and eggs.
Add flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add oats, Rice Krispies and coconut.
Drop cookies on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Store in airtight container.

title: chocolate-covered cherries
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and vanilla until mixture forms a ball. Pinch off marble size ball of dough and flatten on table.
Wrap around cherry, making sure that cherry is well covered. Refrigerate for 4 hours or overnight.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Mix in pie plate the spaghetti, butter, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Press in bottom and up sides slightly.
Spread cottage cheese over spaghetti mixture.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil the potatoes.
Brown the ground beef in skillet; drain excess grease off.
Mix in potatoes after potatoes are cooked, then mix in soup and salt to taste.
If onions are preferred, cook in with ground beef.

title: lesa's crab dip
directions: Mix all this well.
Taste and add spices to taste.
Then carefully pick through 1/2 pound fresh crabmeat.
Add to mixture. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until set.
(Can refrigerate several hours before baking.)
Serve hot with small, sliced French bread.

title: punch for 35 people
directions: Mix well the Jell-O, sugar and boiling water.
Add lemon juice, pineapple juice and cold water.
You can add 1 to 1 1/2 bottles (2-liter) ginger ale and serve or you can make and store in gallon milk container in freezer until party time and then pour ginger ale over frozen punch.

title: batter rolls(easy)
directions: Warm water and sprinkle on yeast; warm milk and melt oleo in it.
Add to yeast mixture along with sugar and egg.
Mix in 2 cups flour with mixer, then add 1 1/2 cups more flour by hand.
Cover and let rise until double, about 45 minutes to an hour.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients until zucchini is evenly coated.
Pour into buttered 10 x 16-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: pineapple-salsa topping
directions: Place frank on bun.
Top each with 4 halved cucumber slices and 2 tablespoons pineapple mixture.

title: best fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and salt.
Boil 5 minutes.
Add and beat in remaining ingredients.
Butter 9 x 9-inch pan.
Pour into it.

title: double delicious cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Melt margarine in 13x9 in. pan. Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs evenly over margarine.
Pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Sprinkle peanut butter & chocolate chips evenly over top.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Let cool then cut into bars. Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: green rice
directions: Mix in order of ingredient list.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: jelly bean confetti cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup.
Level off.

title: pineapple sauce
directions: Beat egg well and add pineapple juice.
Heat until just warm. Add sugar, cornstarch and salt and cook until thickens.
Cool.

title: old timey tea cakes
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, then add flour until mix is stiff (use mixer). Make small balls. Take a flat bottom glass and mash flat. Bake in 350° oven until brown around edges.

title: aunt clara's noodle pudding
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Add 6 tablespoons butter.
Separate eggs. Beat well until stiff, but not dry.
Mix 6 egg yolks, cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream and sugar.
Fold in egg whites. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: mama's spanish chowder
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Add remaining ingredients and cook on low for several hours.
Serve with mashed potatoes and cornbread.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Do not preheat oven.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: skippy fettucini
directions: Combine soups in saucepan.
Cut sausage into desired pieces; add to saucepan.
Bring to simmer.
Cook over low heat for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over noodles.

title: greek chicken salad
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine chicken, cucumber, Feta cheese, olives and parsley; set aside.
For dressing, in a small mixing bowl, stir together Aioli or mayonnaise and garlic mixture, yogurt and oregano.
Add to the chicken mixture.
Toss mixture gently until coated.
Cover and chill.
Serve on Boston lettuce leaves.
Makes 6 servings.

title: wini's cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool.
Cake can be left in pan and served directly from pan.
In saucepan, combine pineapple juice and sugar; boil 5 minutes. Prepare pudding mix as directed on package; refrigerate until ready to use.
When cake is cool, punch holes in it and pour hot pineapple juice over top.
Spread pineapple on top of cake. Spread pudding over pineapple.
Put layer of sliced bananas. Spread Cool Whip over bananas.
Sprinkle with coconut and garnish with nuts.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: banana bread
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 5 loaf pan. Combine all ingredients in large bowl and mix well. Transfer to prepared pan. Bake at 325° until top is golden brown and splits slightly, about 1 hour and 20 minutes. Serve warm.

title: peanut butter delight
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Press into bottom of dish (reserve 1/2 cup).

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix together and put in oblong dish; freeze.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: dutch potatoes
directions: Slice cooled potatoes into thin pieces.
Melt butter in skillet and add potatoes.
Sprinkle flour over and add enough milk to thicken.
Add a few slices of cheese just before serving.
Turn carefully.

title: marinated drumsticks
directions: In a large bowl, combine tomato paste, vinegar, chopped thyme, and soy sauce.
Add drumsticks, turning to coat.
Cover and refrigerate 2-3 hours.

title: lemon dream cake
directions: Bake cake as directed per box.
While cake is warm, poke holes in cake with a wooden spoon handle.
Mix Jell-O with boiling water and pour over cooled cake.
Cool in refrigerator until completely cooled.
Mix pudding with cold milk; add lemon extract and food coloring.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread pudding mix over cooled cake.
Keep cake refrigerated.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions until just tender.
Drain.
Melt butter.
Blend in flour.
Add soup and cream, stirring until thickened.
Add salt and pepper.
Arrange broccoli in a buttered baking dish.
Pour over half the sauce. Arrange chicken on top.
Blend cheese in remaining sauce.
Pour over chicken. Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Broil until golden brown.
Garnish.
Serves 6.

title: italian salad dressing with honey
directions: Put in cruet or jar.
Shake and serve.

title: easy cookies
directions: Blend thoroughly and drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
You may use any flavor cake mix, add nuts, raisins, chocolate chips, or whatever.
My grandsons prefer Funfetti Cake Mix.
Bake about 8 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Mix the chicken soup, enchilada sauce and peppers.
Bring to boil.
In large casserole dish, layer the meat sauce, Doritos and cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cream cream cheese and sugar together. Add pineapple, fruit cocktail and Cool Whip.

title: sausage, kraut and potato casserole
directions: Prepare sausage in covered skillet, using 2/3 to 3/4 cup water.
Simmer 8 to 10 minutes.
Prepare mashed potatoes.
Put sauerkraut in casserole dish, using some of the liquid.
Season, if desired.
Cut sausage into serving pieces and place on the sauerkraut.
Then spoon the mashed potatoes on the sausages. Place casserole in 325° to 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: silver creek salmon potato strata
directions: In large bowl, combine salmon, onion, celery, eggs, milk, 1/2 teaspoon salt, dill and pepper.
Mix well.
Pare potatoes and cut into thin slices.
Place half of potatoes in greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt and spread half of salmon mixture over potatoes.
Repeat with remaining potatoes, salt and salmon.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender when pierced with fork. Remove from oven and let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: fancy rice pudding dessert(fat-free)
directions: Cream together cream cheese, sour cream and vanilla.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over cream cheese mixture and stir. Chill and serve.
Recipe makes 8 servings.

title: three layer mexican dip
directions: Spread beans in 10-inch glass dish.
Cover with guacamole. In bowl, combine next 6 ingredients.
Spread on top of guacamole. Sprinkle with cheese, onions, tomatoes and olives.
Bake 15 minutes in 425° oven.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: eye round roast
directions: Boil roast (simmer, covered with water) for 3 hours.
Take from water; cool and slice into rounds.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil only; pour over roast slices.
Bake, covered, at 300° for 30 minutes.
(I have frozen this after I baked it and it does fine.)

title: aunt ethyl's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, Karo and vanilla.
Line unbaked pie shell with pecans.
Pour mixture carefully into shell.
Bake in slow 325° oven until thoroughly set and firm.

title: oriental cole slaw
directions: Sliver cabbage.
In a saucepan bring vinegar, water, seasoning mix and broth mix (out of noodles) to a boil.
While hot, pour over slivered cabbage.
Stir and serve.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Mix together butter, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add sifted flour and salt; mix thoroughly.
Divide dough in half.
Blend food color and peppermint extract in half of dough.
Chill 1/2 hour.
Make candy cane shapes (twist a red rope around a white rope and shape into candy canes).
Bake at 375° for 9 minutes.

title: carrot raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix cereal, buttermilk and syrup. Let stand 10 minutes. In another bowl combine flour, soda and cinnamon. Add egg, sugar & oil to cereal mixture.
Add cereal mixture to flour mixture and stir until well blended. Stir in carrots. Pour into greased muffin cups. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.	Makes approximately 12 muffins.

title: transfer restaurant's holiday fruit cake
directions: In a
large
bowl,
mix
nuts
and
fruits.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar together and add to nut mixture. Mix well to
coat.
Beat
eggs
well and add rum.
Add this to coated nut mixture and thoroughly blend together.
Pour into 2 greased and floured
bread pans.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Stores well, tightly wrapped and in cool place.

title: roast and brown gravy
directions: Salt and pepper Roast, put in crock pot and cover about 1/2 way with water.
Cook all day if possible.
In a skillet place flour and salt.
Brown to a
medium brown.
Stir constantly.
Set aside and let cool to point that pan is not too hot.
Drain juice from roast and let stand for a minute.
Add to skillet with enough water to reach desired consistency.
Stir out lumps and bring to boil.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: baked pork chops supreme
directions: Salt and pepper chops on both sides.
Brown lightly in the oil.
Place chops in large baking dish.
Cover with celery, onion, mustard, catsup and water.
Spoon generously over each chop. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: Fry onions, green pepper and hamburger meat. Cook noodles. Combine the ingredients and add the can of tomatoes, salt and butter. Cook on low for 1/2 hour.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Combine all ingredients but spaghetti sauce in large bowl. Mix well by hand.
Form baseball sized balls.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with spaghetti sauce, should barely cover all balls in dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: lima bean and pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops and remove from can.
Add 1/4 teaspoon salt, mustard, sugar, pepper, onion, water and puree to dripping and blend well.
Add beans, stir until beans are coated.
Top with the pork chops and sprinkle with remaining salt; bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: lemon fruit cake
directions: Dissolve 1 teaspoon of baking soda in 1 tablespoon of warm water.
Separate eggs.
Beat egg whites (egg yolks are not needed). Combine all ingredients.
For color, add 1 small jar of cherries and 8 ounces of candied pineapple.
Place mixture in a stemmed cake pan, lined fully with brown paper that has been well-buttered.
Bake 2 1/2 hours in a slow oven (300°).

title: pecan tarts
directions: Mix 1/2 cup margarine and 1/2 cup sugar.
Stir in 2 egg yolks, 1 teaspoon almond extract, and 2 cups sifted flour.
Press evenly into tiny tart shells or miniature muffin cups.
Bake in 400°F oven 8-10 minutes.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix and pat in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix altogether.
Grease bottom and sides of baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: macaroni chili
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Put in crock-pot with all other ingredients, except macaroni.
Cook on low 8 to 10 hours.
Cook macaroni and add at the last 20 minutes or so before serving.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Make a well, add warm milk, beaten eggs and oil.
Stir until all flour is mixed.
Knead 1 minute on floured board.
Place in greased bowl and let rise until double in size.
Punch down, make a ball, pinch off balls about 2 inches in diameter and place on greased pan until double in size (second rising).
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for about 15 minutes. Yields 24 rolls.

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Melt the caramels and milk.
Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly.
Pat 3/4 of mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: rice salad
directions: Combine water,	rice, salt and margarine in a saucepan. Cover and cook until rice is tender.
Do not drain!
Add jello and sugar to	hot rice and stir to dissolve.	Mix in pineapple and let cool in	refrigerator.
When
this
begins to set up, fold
in
Cool Whip.
Let	finish	setting
several
hours or overnight.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Drain mandarin oranges and pineapple well. Mix dry Jello, Cool Whip and cottage cheese thoroughly. Add fruit and nuts, mix well. Pour in salad bowl and chill before serving.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Combine flour and next 4 ingredients.
Add to egg mixture.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer, 1 to 2 minutes.
Spoon into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes and remove.
Pour your favorite warm glaze over cake if you like.

title: biscuit nugget chicken bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In medium saucepan, combine chicken, 1/2 teaspoon paprika, dill weed, salt, milk and soup.
Heat until hot and bubbly.
Pour hot chicken mixture into 8 or 9-inch square baking pan.
Separate biscuit dough and cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.

title: chocolate ganache
directions: Heat cream, butter and sugar in a 2 1/2-quart saucepan over medium heat.
Stir to dissolve sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Place the semi-sweet, unsweetened and white chocolate in a steel bowl.
Pour the boiling cream mixture over chocolates.
Let stand 5 minutes. Stir until smooth.
Can put in 1 to 2 teaspoons vanilla, pecans or orange rind (optional).
Refrigerate.
Cut into bite-size pieces.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking soda; set aside.
In large bowl, with electric mixer at medium-high speed, cream margarine and granulated sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, yogurt and peel.
Beat 1 to 2 minutes until mixture is smooth.
Stir in dry ingredients and thoroughly combine.
Spray a Bundt pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Spread batter evenly in pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.
Let cool in pan on rack for 15 minutes.
Loosen edges and invert cake onto rack to cool completely.

title: fried green ramps
directions: In a large cast-iron frying pan, heat cooking oil; add ramps. Cover and cook on lowest heat.
Stir once or twice; fry 35 minutes or until tender.
Best served with fried fatback, or bacon strips, scrambled eggs, fried potatoes and corn bread.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Cook pineapple juice, egg, sugar and flour until thick.
Allow to cool.
Combine pineapple chunks and marshmallows.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick of margarine or butter (softened) and press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat 10x sugar, eggs and 2 sticks of margarine or butter (softened) for 15 minutes until stiff.
Spread this over graham cracker crumbs.

title: louise's fried shrimp
directions: Peel shrimp and dry on paper towels, top and bottom.
Devein shrimp, if you like.
Combine ingredients, adding water last.
As you stir mixture should be consistency of pancake batter or thinner.
On a separate plate, crush cornflakes with your hands. Do not use bought crumbs as they are too fine.
Dip each shrimp in batter and roll in cornflake crumbs.
Crush more flakes, if necessary.
Cook in a deep fat fryer in Crisco, about 8 to 12 shrimp at the time, for 1 minute.
Drain on paper towels and serve.

title: creole coconut pie
directions: Beat whites until stiff.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar.
Cream butter and remaining sugar.
Add yolks and blend thoroughly.
Add milk and vanilla.
Fold whitened coconut into butter mixture. Pour into pie shell.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: mock chocolate eclair
directions: Prepare pudding with milk; fold in Cool Whip.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch dish and place 1 layer of crackers as is.
Add 1/2 vanilla mixture, then another layer of crackers, then the rest of pudding mixture and the final layer of crackers.

title: strawberry daiquiri
directions: Blend in blender and top with whipped cream.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; add milk.
Pour into deep dish in which oleo has been melted.
Add peaches.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until crust is golden brown.
Very good.

title: chicken curry
directions: Wash the chicken and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Heat oil in a Dutch oven.
Add chicken and brown over medium heat.
Remove and reserve chicken.
Add onions, cinnamon stick, cardamom and cloves to pan.
Saute until onions are lightly browned.
Add more oil if needed.
Add turmeric, chili powder, coriander, ginger, garlic, cumin and bay leaves.
Fry spices 4 to 5 minutes, sprinkling with water if they become too dry.
Stir in ketchup and return chicken to pan.
Pour in water and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer over low heat until chicken is tender and sauce is thickened, about 30 minutes.
Serve with rice or bread.
Yields 4 servings.

title: breakfast casserole(great for dinner, too)
directions: Cut up bacon and fry until crisp.
Drain grease and set aside. Mix hash browns, eggs and sour cream.
Add bacon and cheese.
Add salt, pepper and seasonings to desired taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mcgaro's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to boil.
Thicken with flour and water, if desired.
Makes 1 pint.

title: saul's spice cake
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, combine raisins, sugar, cinnamon and water and bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Stir in the butter; set aside to cool.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, cloves and salt.
Add flour mixture to cooled sugar-water mixture and mix well.
Turn batter into lightly greased tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake tester comes out clean.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: holiday cranberry conserve
directions: Grate orange peel; cut oranges in half.
Remove seeds and chop coarsely.
Place grated peel and chopped pulp in blender with the water.
Blend about 1 minute, until finely ground.

Pour mixture into a saucepan and cook covered over medium flame for 20 minutes. Add cranberries, sugar, raisins and salt; boil rapidly uncovered over medium-high flame until mixture drops from spoon in a sheet, leaving the spoon clean.
Stir in nuts and cook 5 minutes longer, stirring gently to avoid scorching.
Chill.
Serve in a pretty crystal bowl.
Yield:
3 to 4 cups.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread in a 9x13 cake pan or casserole dish. Spread topping of 2 cups crushed cornflakes or potato chips and melted oleo. Bake at 375° for one hour.

title: walnut sour cream fudge
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, salt, cream and butter in
heavy skillet.
Boil without stirring to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and let stand 10 minutes.
Do not stir.
Add flavoring and beat until creamy.
Stir in walnuts.
Quickly pour into greased pan.
Watch when beating and when it begins to thicken, add nuts and pour out or it will be a big chunk.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and salad oil; bring to boil.
Cool.
After squeezing juice from sauerkraut, cut fine with shears or scissors. Toss green pepper, celery and onions with sauerkraut.
Pour cooled liquid over vegetables.
Seal in container and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: tofu tamale pie
directions: Mix and simmer all but last 3 ingredients until tender.
Add tofu and cornmeal. Pour into baking dish and top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly on top.

title: irene's salad dressing
directions: Mix first six ingredients and let set for 1/2 hour.
Blend oil and vinegar and beat well.
Store in refrigerator.
Best after sitting for several hours.
A blender may be used.

title: sidewalk chalk
directions: You will also need wax paper and toilet paper cores or paper towel cores, cut in 4-inch lengths.

title: easy yeast rolls(muffin)
directions: Mix yeast and water. Stir in remaining ingredients and pour into muffin pans. Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix catsup and mustard.
Add vinegar, sugar, margarine, salt, pepper and lemon
juice.
Simmer
for about 1 hour.
Add Worcestershire, soy sauce and black pepper.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: In first bowl, combine jello and boiling water and set aside. In second bowl, beat eggs; add sugar, whipping cream, vanilla and pudding.
Whip together.
Add milk and mix well.
Combine with jello mixture to which I've added the fruit.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Crumble bacon in pie crust along with cheese and onion.
Beat eggs with remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 30 minutes or until knife inserted 1 inch from edge comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix with 3 cups milk until smooth, then stir in Eagle Brand milk.
Layer vanilla wafers in bottom of oblong pan or dish, then layer of pudding mix, bananas and Cool Whip. Continue until all is used, ending with Cool Whip on top.

title: zeb's old fashion tea cakes
directions: Add sugar, butter, flour, salt and vanilla with beaten eggs. Flour hands.
Take dough for each cake and pat.
Place in greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients.
Chill.
Using 1/2 tsp. mixture for each, roll into 24 balls.
Place in 1 1/2 inch paper bonbon cups.
Melt coating and remaining peanut butter over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Spoon into cups to fill.
Chill.
Makes 2 doz.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions.
Bake 1/2 cake mix for 15 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt caramels with milk and margarine; pour over baked cake.
Sprinkle nuts and chips over mix.
Top with remaining cake batter.
Bake for about 25 minutes more, or until top cake batter is done.

title: pigs in the blanket casserole
directions: Put thick layer of cabbage in bottom of casserole dish.
Brown meat and onion; add rice, salt and pepper.
Spread over cabbage.
Repeat another layer of cabbage, then layer of meat mixture.
Pour soup mixed with water over all.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy chicken parmesan
directions: Dip chicken into egg.
Coat with bread crumbs.
In skillet, over medium heat, heat oil.
Cook chicken 10 minutes or until done.
Set chicken aside.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Brown pieces of chicken and place in baking pan.
Sprinkle with salt.
Sprinkle uncooked rice over chicken.
Mix soups and water and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: summertime breakfast spread
directions: Mix cheese, raisins, nuts and seasonings together.
Store in a covered container in the refrigerator.
When ready to serve, spread the mixture on bread or muffin halves.
Broil until bubbly.

title: hanky panky's
directions: Cook and brown meat.
Drain fat.
Add cut up cheese, garlic salt, oregano and mushrooms.
Spoon on bread.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine corn, cheese, egg substitute and pimento in large bowl. Stir well.
Combine 1 cup milk and flour in a small bowl; stir until smooth.
Add remaining 1 cup milk, sugar and next 3 ingredients.
Stir well.
Add flour mixture to corn.
Mix and pour into 2-quart casserole coated with cooking spray.
Place this pan in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan filled with water.
Baked uncovered at 325° for 30 minutes.
Add chopped pepper.
Bake an additional 50 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Contains 4.5 grams fat per serving.

title: molasses stack cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil, molasses and buttermilk. Put all dry ingredients in separate bowl. Mix together. If too thin to work, add self-rising flour. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Cook milk, margarine and sugar over medium heat until soft-ball stage; remove from heat and add vanilla, marshmallow cream, chocolate chips or peanut butter chips.
May also add chopped nuts.

title: fudge cake
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together over low heat (or in microwave for 2 minutes). Combine with other ingredients.
Mix well and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch dish. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a medium size casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Bake 55 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serves 15.
Recipe may be halved.

title: delicious pear jam
directions: Cook pears; mash and drain. Add sugar, Jell-O, lemon juice and pineapple. Cook until it jells and stir, stir, stir. Pour into hot jars and seal.

title: no-peek casserole
directions: Mix together and bake in heavy covered pan or casserole for 3 hours at 300° and don't peek!
Serve over rice or buttered noodles.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Add milk and coloring.
Fold in soda and vinegar.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: jello punch
directions: Mix jello.
Add remaining ingredients.
Just before serving, add 2 quarts of ginger ale.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: oysterette cracker snacks
directions: Heat oil and seasonings.
Add crackers.
Stir constantly until oil is gone.
If you double recipe, use only 1 1/2 cups oil.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt in ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Mix in milk, oil and vanilla with fork until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Pour hot water over batter.
Bake for 40 minutes.
While warm, spoon into dessert dishes; top with ice cream.
Spoon sauce from pan onto each serving.
Makes 9 servings.

title: no cook cocoa oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together sugar and cocoa. Add milk and mix. Add butter and cook to boiling and boil 1 minute. Remove from heat. Stir in 1/2 c. peanut butter, 3 c.
quick oats and 1/2 tsp. vanilla. Stir thoroughly and drop by spoonful on waxed paper. Let cool.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Cream the cheese and sugar and set aside.
Bake pretzels and melted butter in a 9 x 11-inch or an 8 x 13 1/2-inch baking dish at 400° for 10 minutes.
Do not overbrown.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Heat cherry and pineapple juices.
Dissolve Jell-O in juice. Add pineapple, cherries and nuts.
Add Coca-Cola; mix and pour into dish to gel.
Chill until firm.

title: light grits spoon bread
directions: Combine milk, grits and salt in a heavy saucepan.
Cook 10
to 12
minutes
on low heat, stirring constantly or until very thick.
Beat
egg yolks.
Add a little hot grits to warm egg yolks.
Add
yolks	to grits.
Beat egg whites until they form stiff
peaks.
Fold
into
grits
mixture.	Put in 1 1/2 quart casserole dish sprayed with cooking spray.	Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until lightly brown.	Serves 6.

title: cheese quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: crunchy onion chicken
directions: Crush onion pieces with a rolling pin on a large flat surface. Dip the chicken in the egg/milk mixture, then firmly coat with the crushed onion pieces.
Place the chicken in an ungreased baking pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: low-fat chicken casserole
directions: Boil noodles as directed using some chicken broth.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake around 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: rhubarb cake with oatmeal crust
directions: Work all ingredients together like pie crust.
Line a 13 x 9-inch baking dish with the mixture and reserve 1 cup for topping. Slice rhubarb or apples (1/2-inch pieces) into pan.

title: hot wings
directions: Cut off and discard tips of chicken wings.
Rinse pieces and pat dry.
Fry wing pieces in deep hot oil until crispy and golden brown and no longer pink.
Set aside.
In a saucepan melt butter, stir in honey and Texas Pete wing sauce.
Heat and add wings turning to coat.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mash one pint grapes, cook in juice, run through colander, add one cup sugar, tablespoon cornstarch; cook in double boiler.
Bake crust on inverted pan; beat white of one egg, one spoon sugar, spread over top, set in oven and brown slightly.

title: marinated chicken stir-fry
directions: Cut chicken in bite size chunks. Marinate for 3 to 4 hours in Italian dressing.
Saute chicken in hot wok. After chicken has cooked, remove from wok.
Add vegetables to wok.
Stir, coating vegetables with dressing.
Cook until vegetables become tender. Return chicken to wok.
Stir and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes. Drain excess dressing and serve over hot spaghetti.
May add soy sauce to taste.

title: chicken and mushrooms
directions: Brown chicken on medium heat for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add mushrooms, garlic, basil, and wine.
Continue to cook for 30 minutes or until thoroughly cooked.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Combine yogurt, buttermilk and mayonnaise substitute in a small bowl, stirring until blended.
Stir in pickle, catsup, parsley and seasoned salt.
Cover and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Combine boiling water, sugar and shortening; set aside to cool.
Mix warm water with yeast and eggs; then add flour and cooled water, shortening and sugar; mix well.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out dough on a floured surface.
Cut out in favorite shape.
Let rise in pan until double in size, about 4 hours in a warm place.
Bake at 400°.

title: mexican haystack dip
directions: Spread bean dip on large round platter.
Mix frozen avocado dip and fresh mashed avocados and lemon juice together, spread on the bean dip.

title: walnut bourbon or rum balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Add syrup and bourbon or rum and mix well.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Then roll in sifted powdered sugar.

title: five layer casserole dinner
directions: Take a 9 x 13-inch glass casserole dish and spray with Pam nonstick spray.
Mash ground beef into bottom of pan.
Peel potatoes, slice thinly and place over top of ground beef.
Slice onions in rings.
Place over potatoes.
Chop bell pepper and place over onions.
Pour water over entire casserole.
Top with 2 cups shredded Velveeta cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: date nut roll
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl; mix well. Divide mixture in half; shape each half into an 8 x 1-inch roll. Wrap rolls in wax paper and chill overnight.
To serve, slice as desired.

title: oven chicken
directions: Dip chicken into butter.
Roll in a mixture of bread crumbs and cheese.
Place chicken pieces, skin side up and not touching, into 2 large, shallow, greased, baking pans.
Top with remaining butter and crumb mixture.
Bake at 375° until done, about 1 hour. Serves 8.

title: brownie pie
directions: Beat eggs and salt until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Fold in cookie crumbs, vanilla and nuts.
Bake in buttered pie pan at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool and add 1 cup whipping cream.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Drain canned vegetables.
Chop onion and green pepper.
Boil vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and water; cool.
Mix all vegetables, onion, pepper (green) and pimento.
Pour liquid ingredients over vegetables; refrigerate overnight.
Drain before serving.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into pie shells.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°; bake 30 to 40 minutes longer, until knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: quick fruit pie
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Mix flour and other dry ingredients with 1 c. sugar and milk.
Stir until well blended. Pour batter into casserole with butter.
Add 3/4 c. sugar to fruit and heat.
Pour into batter.
Bake in 350° oven until browned.

title: calico beans
directions: Pour beans into casserole dish. Combine next 7 ingredients and 1/2 of the butter. Cook sauce until onion is tender.
Pour sauce over beans.
Pour remaining butter over sauce.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: florentine brunch casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut crusts off bread using serrated bread knife.
Cube crusts to measure 2 cups.
Arrange bread slices in an overlapping pattern against sides of Oval Baker; place bread cubes in bottom.
Place 2 tablespoons of the butter in Small Micro-Cooker; microwave, covered, on High 30 seconds or until melted.
Lightly brush butter over bread slices using Pastry Brush.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until edges of bread are golden brown.

title: heaven
directions: Pour over cream cheese layer.
Spread Cool Whip on top. Sprinkle with nuts.

title: the ruby slipper
directions: Combine cake mix, sour cream, water and eggs in a large bowl. Blend, then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes until creamy. Spoon 1/3 of batter into well-greased and floured 10-inch fluted tube pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 the gelatin.
Repeat layers.
Spread remaining batter over gelatin to cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, until cake springs back when lightly pressed.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes.
Remove from pan, cool on rack.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: cupcakes elegant
directions: Melt chocolate and oleo; add pecans.
Stir well to coat pecans.
Combine sugar, flour, eggs and vanilla.
Stir until blended, but do not beat.
Add chocolate-nut mixture.
Stir, but do not beat.
Fill cupcake liners 2/3 full.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: fried pie
directions: Cut in butter into flour with pastry blender.
Combine milk and egg.
Pour egg over flour mixture and mix well.
Roll out small portion onto floured surface.
Place in pie filling center. Fold over and seal edges with water.
Fry in deep hot fat until golden brown.

title: hot salsa
directions: Place all vegetables in a large skillet. Stir. Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil and simmer 30 minutes. Seal or freeze.

title: reuben dip
directions: Chop corned beef into bite size pieces.
Add cheeses and sauerkraut.
Add mayonnaise or Thousand Island dressing to the consistency of tuna salad.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 40 minutes.
Serve with party rye.

title: three day crock pickles
directions: Although any size cucumber may be used, it's a good way to use the large ones.
Wash and make about 3 slits down the sides of each cucumber.
Place in a large container, such as a crock or wide mouth gallon jars (no metal containers).
Add some dill pieces, fresh garlic (sliced), and chilie pitins (as many as you like).

title: easy crumb cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a bowl and add butter to mix to fine crumbs.
Take away 1 cup of crumbs for topping - add cinnamon to taste, and set aside.
Add eggs and milk to the remainder of the batter and mix.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 baking pan, sprinkle the reserved crumb mixture over the top and bake for 1/2 hour at 375 degrees.

title: carol's barbecue salmon
directions: Place fish in
tubs
made out of aluminum foil. Combine mayonnaise, soy sauce
and	pour
over fish. Slice onions into 1/4-inch thick rings;
layer
over fish.
It's o.k. to overlap onions evenly over fish. Rinse and shake dry dill weed.
Place these whole branches thickly over fish.
Barbecue with lid on, very short time on	a hot fire, about 15 minutes.
Remove dill branches and serve.

title: sausage-wild rice casserole
directions: Thaw turkey in refrigerator.
Place whole or halved orange in cavity. Rub turkey with salt and pepper.
Place turkey in large roasting pan.
Seal with foil. Bake at 250° overnight. Moist.

title: beef stew
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper in pie pan.
Dredge meat in flour mixture.
In a large heavy saucepan, melt shortening.
Add beef. Cook until browned on both sides. Add water and simmer, covered, for 90 minutes. Stir occasionally. Add soup, onions, carrots and potatoes. Cook 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: ruth's pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, and salt together.
Stir in syrup.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix in milk, pecans and vanilla.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375 degrees for 50 minutes.
If recipe is doubled, makes 3 pies.

title: pork and potato stew
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven over medium heat until hot.
Add pork, carrots and onions.
Cook until pork is browned.
Drain.
Add potatoes, bouillon, pork seasoning, 4 cups of the water and vinegar.
Mix well.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
In small bowl, combine remaining 1/4 cup water and flour.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended.
Add flour mixture and cabbage to stew.
Mix well.
Cover.
Simmer 10 minutes or until stew is thickened.

title: caramel chocolate pie
directions: Sprinkle
gelatin over water in a small saucepan.
Stir over low
heat
until
completely dissolved.
Blend in 2/3 cup whipping cream
and
bring
mixture to a boil.
Put in blender and add chocolate chips.
Process until chips are melted.
Add 1/3 cup whipping
cream, eggs and vanilla, mixing well.
Pour into a bowl and chill until thickened, about 15 minutes.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Pour champagne and 7-Up into punch bowl.
Drop in scoops of pineapple sherbet.

title: foolproof slow roast turkey
directions: Defrost and clean turkey.
Tie wings and legs to sides of turkey using 100% cotton string (this helps the turkey to cook more evenly and also holds the turkey together since it becomes very tender).

title: brittany's waffles
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine egg yolks, milk and oil.
Mix into dry ingredients.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in your favorite waffle iron.

title: beef tenderloin marinade
directions: Mix ingredients together and marinate beef overnight.
Turn several times to ensure that all of tenderloin is covered.
Set oven to broil and place meat on cookie sheet.
Place in oven and reduce heat to 450°.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: fungi
directions: Boil okra and salt for 3 minutes.
Add remaining boiling water and sprinkle corn meal in slowly.
Allow water to boil over meal a few minutes.
Stir briskly to prevent lumping.
When well combined, add shortening.
Cover; steam about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve hot.
Serve with steamed fish.

title: raspberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; let cool.
Add raspberries and applesauce.
Mix and pour into pan, Tupperware or glass container approximately 7 x 11-inches.
Let set until firm.
Mix sour cream and marshmallows and spread over jello.
Let set for several more hours.
Cut in 2 x 3-inch squares.
Serve with a sprig of mint. Good with poultry and pork.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Brown meat in large skillet; drain grease.
Add enchilada sauce, both soups, chilies and rice.
With low heat, mix until all ingredients are blended.
Crush Doritos in the bag.
In a 9 x 12-inch baking dish, layer 1/2 Doritos, 1/2 meat mixture and layer remainder of mixture.
Top with shredded cheese.
It is ready to serve.

title: italian spaghetti sauce(no salt)
directions: Tomatoes may be crushed or blended (briefly).
Remove bay leaf when finished cooking.
Cook sauce until desired thickness. This freezes well.
Prepare as many tomatoes as you have; add other ingredients for each quart of tomatoes.

title: strawberry pound cake
directions: Mix together,
batter will be heavy.
Bake in greased tube pan at 325° for one hour.
Let stand 15-20 minutes.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Cook ground chuck; drain well and set aside.
Mix next 5 ingredients.
Grease baking dish.
Put half the corn bread mixture in pan; add in layers the meat, onion and peppers and cheese. Cover with remainder of corn bread mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook about 3 hours.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix sugar, egg, flour, butter and pineapple in a casserole. Put bread cubes in.
Make sure they are all submerged so they don't burn.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 1/2 hour.
A great side dish for ham or pork roast.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix together 1/2 cup sugar and lemon juice.
Let stand.
Cream together oleo, 1 cup sugar, eggs, lemon rind, milk, flour, baking powder and salt.
Pour creamed ingredients into a loaf pan and bake 45 to 55 minutes in a 350° oven.
Pour lemon juice and sugar mixture over warm loaf.
Let cool in pan.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Drain juice from strawberries.
Reserve strawberries.
Mix juice with cake mix, eggs, oil, water and jello.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix together, adding 3 cups of rhubarb last.
Put in pie shell.
Mix 1/2 cup flour, 1/4 cup brown sugar and 1/4 cup butter into crumbs and spread on pie.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until done.

title: fabulous potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: quick christmas jam
directions: Combine apricot, pineapple and peach preserves. Add orange marmalade, maraschino cherries and green cherries.
Stir until evenly mixed.

title: sweet and sour sauce for cabbage
directions: Cook sauce until like thin custard.
Pour over hot cooked cabbage.

title: german chocolate cake
