directions: Mix flour cocoa, salt and baking soda together before adding to first 5 ingredients.
Combine everything with electric mixer. Pour into greased cookie sheet or two 9 x 12 greased cake pans. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Mix together oleo, flour and 1/2 cup nuts; press in bottom of pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: apple squares
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients by hand to make crumb mixture.
Set aside all but one cup of it.
Grease 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan and put this one cup of mixture in bottom of pan.
Take sliced apples and sprinkle the sugar/cinnamon over it.
Layer pan with apples (2 layers) and sprinkle remaining crumb mixture (any left-over sugar/cinnamon can be added to crumb mixture).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool completely and cut into squares.

title: zesty stuffed zucchini
directions: Preheat oven to moderate 350°.
Lightly grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch square baking dish.
Cook zucchini in boiling, salted water to cover in large saucepan for 5 minutes.
Drain; cut lengthwise slice from each zucchini to within 1-inch of ends.
Scoop out pulp with spoon, leaving 1/4-inch shell.
Coarsely chop pulp and slices.
Combine zucchini, pulp, bread stuffing, Blue cheese and pepper in small bowl.
Stuff mixture into zucchini shells, mounding on top.
Place in baking dish. Dot with butter.
Bake in preheated moderate oven (350°) for 25 to 30 minutes or until stuffing is lightly browned.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken divan casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling salted water until tender; drain. Arrange broccoli in greased baking dish.
Place chicken on top. Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs and butter. Sprinkle over all.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Trim with pimento strips.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs, milk, vanilla, sugars and flour; beat well.
Add butter; mixing well.
Stir in pecans; pour filling into shell. Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Yields one pie or 8 tarts.

title: pasta with shrimp and vegetables
directions: About 40 minutes before serving:

In nonstick 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in 1 tablespoon hot olive or salad oil, cook shrimp, green onions, grated ginger, garlic and 1/4 teaspoon salt, stirring constantly until shrimp are opaque throughout, about 3 minutes.
With slotted spoon, remove shrimp mixture to bowl.

In dripping remaining in skillet and 1 teaspoon additional hot olive or salad oil, cook carrots, yellow pepper and 1/4 teaspoon salt, stirring frequently, until vegetables are golden and tender-crisp.

title: cinnamon pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and salt in small bowl.
Whisk egg whites in large bowl until frothy.
Add pecans and toss to coat.
Add sugar mixture and toss thoroughly. Spread pecans in a single layer on a large cookie sheet.
Bake until toasted and crisp, about 20 minutes.
Using spatula, loosen pecans from cookie sheet.
Cool.
Can be prepared 2 weeks ahead. Store in airtight containers.

title: pineapple squares
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar and cook until thick; cool.
Mix together flour, baking powder, sugar and salt; cut in shortening. Add egg yolk and milk; mix.
Divide dough in half, roll out to size and put in small cookie sheet.
Add pineapple filling.
Roll out other half of dough to size and cover filling with it.
Beat egg white and brush over top of dough.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° or until brown.

title: butterscotch swirl ring cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heavily grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Reserve 3 tablespoons pudding mix for glaze.
Put dry cake mix, remaining pudding mix, water, eggs and 1/4 cup butter into large mixer bowl.
Prepare cake as directed on package.
Reserve 1 cup batter; spread remainder evenly in pan.
Blend reserved batter, brown sugar and flour; spoon in ring onto batter.
Using spoon, fold brown sugar mixture into batter; go around pan twice and avoid scraping sides of pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes; cake is done if toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 25 minutes; invert on serving plate.

title: cauliflower polonaise(servings:  6 to 8)
directions: Trim base from cauliflower and remove leaves.
Cook in boiling, salted water for 10 to 15 minutes, or until tender. Drain.
Lightly brown butter and stir in bread crumbs, egg, parsley and seasonings.
Pour over cauliflower.

title: german sugar cake
directions: Dough can also be used as stolen with fruit and nuts added.

title: john's fantastic peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix milk, butters, sugars and salt in heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 6 minutes, stirring all the while.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and powdered sugar.
Beat with mixture until smooth and thick, about 6 minutes.
Pour into buttered pan and freeze for 20 minutes. Cut into pieces.
Makes a little more than a pound.

title: green jello salad
directions: Prepare jello according to package directions with 2 cups of hot water; add pineapple (do not drain) and sugar.
Mix and chill.

title: date roll
directions: Cook flour, sugar and milk until it forms a hard ball.
Add dates, nuts and butter.
Beat.
Roll in damp cloth.
Chill and slice.

title: mustard pickle
directions: Thickening:
Use 4 to 8 tablespoons flour with 2 to 4 teaspoons turmeric.

title: quesadillas
directions: Heat oil in deep skillet.
Put 2 tablespoons cheese and 1 teaspoon chilies in each tortilla.
Fold tortillas in half; use 3 toothpicks in each tortilla to hold closed.
Deep-fry in hot oil 1 minute on each side.
Using tongs, remove and put on paper towel to drain and cool.
Makes a great snack or side dish.

title: vegetable stock
directions: Heat the oil in a 6-quart pressure cooker over medium-high heat. Add the leeks, garlic and onion. Cook until leeks are tender and the onion begins to brown, about 5 minutes. Scrape the caramelized crust from pan with a wooden spoon, if necessary. Add the carrots, celery and parsnips and cook 5 minutes more. Add the squash, potatoes, tomato, bay leaves, parsley, peppercorns and water. Lock the lid in place and bring the cooker to high pressure. Reduce the heat to maintain high pressure and cook 12 minutes. Release the pressure naturally, if time permits. Strain the stock through a strainer, pressing the vegetables against the side to release as much flavor and liquid as possible. Discard the solids. Season to taste with salt, if needed. Makes 10 cups stock.

title: fruit salad
directions: In double boiler, melt milk and cream cheese.
Add milk and beat.
Add vanilla pudding.
Drain fruit cocktail and add to mixture with marshmallows.
Chill.

title: potpourri panels
directions: Have you child draw a picture on poster board with markers. Have your child paint over portions of their picture with the glue. Before glue dries, sprinkle different spices on the sticky areas. Allow to dry.
Pictures will delight the eyes and the nose!

title: salad lunch
directions: Mix last 4 ingredients.
Place a portion on each slice of ham and roll up jelly roll fashion.
Secure and chill.
Serve with garnish of green grapes or fruit in season.

title: marinated carrots(serves 4)
directions: Mix all together, except carrots.
Cook 7 minutes.
Add carrots and marinate 24 hours. Reheat when ready to serve.
"Great to make ahead."

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter.
Add sugar and cream.
Add flour and quick oatmeal and beat.
Mix together.
Roll in balls. Indent with fork.
Bake about 12 minutes in 350° oven.
When cookies are cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Pour rice into casserole.
Place chicken parts on rice.
Add water to soups.
Pour onto chicken and rice.
Cover with foil. Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until chicken is done.

title: senators crab cake
directions: Form into patties. Fry in oil until heated through.

title: pasta salad
directions: Prepare spaghetti according to directions.
Wash and slice vegetables.
Add all ingredients to spaghetti.
Serve chilled.

title: apple dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours. Enjoy!

title: fresh cranberry salad
directions: Add 1 cup water to cranberries and cook until cranberries pop. Add cherry Jell-O and sugar; mix and let set until cool.
Add oranges, apples and pineapple; mix well and refrigerate.

title: frito pie
directions: Brown and simmer the first 7 ingredients.
Add to mixture tomato sauce and water.
In casserole dish, put layer of Fritos, layer of mixture, layer of cheese.
Bake 1 hour slowly at 350°.

title: grilled cheese sandwiches
directions: Heat frying pan to 350 degrees till golden brown.
Butter both sides of each slice of bread.
Put one slice in pan and put cheese on top, then put bread on top of that.
Brown on both sides.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Cut the steak in pencil-thin strips 2 inches long.
Heat the oil in a heavy skillet; brown the meat in it.
Mix in the salt, pepper, green onions, garlic, green peppers and celery.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring almost continuously.
Stir in the broth; cook over low heat 5 minutes.
Mix together the cornstarch and soy sauce until smooth; add to the meat mixture and bring to the boiling point, stirring steadily.
Cook 3 minutes longer.
Serve with rice or noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: peanut butter crisscrosses
directions: Thoroughly cream the shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla. Stir in peanut butter.
Sift dry ingredients; stir into creamed mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Press crisscross pattern with floured fork.
Bake for 10 minutes on top oven shelf at 350°.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients, then add the eggs.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: griddle prawns
directions: Heat the
griddle
and add a portion of the butter.
As the butter
melts,
add
some garlic and green onions.
As you start to smell
the aroma, add the prawns.
You don't want the griddle too hot
and
want the prawns to cook evenly while you constantly turn them.
As you turn the prawns, use the spatula to drip the cooking butter over the meat.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Press into an 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: steak bake
directions: Arrange steak in casserole dish.
Mix cream of mushroom soup and water.
Pour over steak.
Sprinkle onion soup mix on top. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths.
Mix in brown sugar and cinnamon. Put in greased pan.
Put remaining brown sugar, cinnamon, butter and vanilla in a bowl.
Melt.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs and buttermilk together.
Add remaining ingredients. Beat well; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour in a 325° oven.

title: waffles
directions: Beat egg yolks well; stir in milk.
Sift together dry ingredients; add melted margarine.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form when batter is raised.
Fold in butter.
Bake in hot waffle iron.
Makes 6 to 8 waffles.

title: cheese crock
directions: Combine cream cheese and olive oil.
Add dry mustard and caraway seed.
Blend.
After 1st batch, add grated pieces of cheese.
Add few drops of liqueur.
Cover and refrigerate.
Keep enough booze in to forstall molding.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Mix milk and pudding 1 to 2 minutes with whisk; let set for 5 minutes.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Cover pan with a layer of cookie crumbs.
Add pudding, then top with remaining crumbs.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: 5 thing rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a greased 2-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate brownie pie
directions: Mix and pour in greased pie pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix well and pour into serving bowl.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: creamy lemon cheese cake
directions: Measure 1 cup dry cake mix; set aside.
Combine remaining mix with 1 egg and oil.
Press in bottom of a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Combine reserved mix, 2 eggs and remaining ingredients.
Beat at low speed for 2 minutes.
Spread over crust. Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco until fluffy.
Add sugar and beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Sift flour and soda together.
Add to mixture alternately with buttermilk. Add vanilla, nuts and coconut.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in 3 well-greased and floured pans at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Put vanilla wafer in foil cup and add mixture.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
May be topped with canned pie filling, then refrigerate.

title: easy punch
directions: Makes 2 1/2 quarts; 80 ounces; 20 (4 ounce) servings.

title: creamy ham and broccoli
directions: If desired, coat inside of slow-cooker with non-stick spray. In slow cooker, place ham, broccoli, soup, cheese spread, rice, milk, celery, onion, and pepper. Stir until blended. Smooth top, pushing rice into mixture.

title: maryland crab fondue
directions: Remove all cartilage from crab meat.
Combine cheeses, milk, seasonings and sherry in fondue pot.
Set on low.
Stir until blended and smooth.
Add crab meat; heat, stirring occasionally, until hot and bubbly, 5 to 10 minutes.
Spear cubes of bread with a fondue fork and swirl with a figure-eight motion to coat.
(If fondue thickens while standing, stir in a little additional milk or sherry.)

title: vodka slush
directions: Mix and freeze.
Serve several scoops in glass with ice and 7-Up.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order given and put in small balls on ungreased cookie sheet, baking in moderate oven until light brown.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix together peanuts, sugar and syrup.	Cook on High 8 minutes. Stir after 4 minutes.
After 8 minutes, add vanilla and butter and cook 2 minutes.
Add baking soda.
Stir quickly and pour into flat pan.
Allow to cool and break into pieces.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients well and put in deep dish to bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: filet au poivre
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Make slits with a paring knife on all sides of filet.
Insert garlic slices.
Rub filet with olive oil. Press pepper onto surface of beef.
Place on rack in shallow roasting pan.
Roast in preheated 450° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350°.
Roast another 35 minutes or until thermometer inserted in beef registers 130° for rare or cook 10 minutes long (140°) for medium.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.

title: hot fruit compote
directions: Grate rind of orange and lemon into brown sugar.
Spread fruits, layer by layer including orange and lemon sliced very thin into a baking dish.
Sprinkle each layer with brown sugar mixture and a generous sprinkling of nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve warm topped with whipped cream.
Good also served as a dish to accompany pork.

title: kashmiri pulao rice
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add rice. Stir.
Cover pan, lower heat and simmer for 20 minutes. Remove lid and stir rice well.
Remove to platter and allow to cool.
Mix cooled rice with sugar, salt, garlic powder and mint.
Set aside.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Partially thaw bread dough; break into small pieces (I cut it with scissors).
Place into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix melted margarine, brown sugar, pudding, milk and cinnamon; pour over bread.
(Place chopped nuts over batter at this time if using them.)
Let rise for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: sock it to me sour cream butter cake
directions: Place cake mix in mixing bowl; add sugar, oil, butter, sour cream and eggs, beaten 1 at a time.
Place 1/2 of batter in greased and floured tube pan.
Mix cinnamon and brown sugar and pecans (optional); sprinkle on batter in pan.
Place remaining batter on top and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: lite oreo dessert
directions: Crush Oreos and set aside a small bowl of Oreos.
Pour the rest in a 9 x 11-inch pan.
Melt 1 cup margarine and pour over Oreos to form a crust.

title: potato salad
directions: Cube potatoes.
Add eggs, onions, pickles, parsley and celery seed.
Mix mayonnaise and sour cream.
Layer potatoes, then cream mixture, ending with cream mixture on top.
Sprinkle with paprika. Refrigerate.

title: birthday cones
directions: Read the book Happy Birthday, Moon or A Birthday For Frances.

title: mississippi pecan tarts
directions: Prepare pastry for one-crust pie as directed on package, except divide dough into 6 equal parts.
Shape each into ball and roll into 4-inch circles.
Ease into muffin cups, making pleats so pastry will fit closely.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix and chill before serving.

title: spoon bread
directions: Heat 2 cups milk over medium-high heat in a heavy saucepan to 180° or until tiny bubbles form around the edge (do not boil!). Place cornmeal in a bowl.

Add remaining 1/4 cup milk, margarine, salt and pepper, stirring until well blended; add to saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat, stirring constantly with a wire whisk, and cook 2 minutes or until thickened.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Beat egg substitute in a small bowl at high speed of an electric mixer for 2 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Add egg substitute to cornmeal mixture; stir until well blended.
Pour mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until puffed and set; serve immediately.
Yield: 4 servings of 3/4 cup each.

title: bottom's up cake
directions: Heat oven to 350° and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread frosting into bottom of prepared pan.
Sprinkle nuts over frosting.
In large bowl blend cake mix, water, oil and eggs.
Beat 2 minutes at highest speed.
Pour batter over frosting in pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Immediately invert pan onto serving plate.
Serve warm or cold. Yields 12 servings.

title: skillet salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove from skillet; pour off fat, except for 1 tablespoonful.
Combine onion, salt, brown sugar and vinegar in tablespoon of drippings left in skillet.
Toss parsley and cabbage in hot drippings.
Add crumbled bacon.
Heat thoroughly.
Serves 4.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon butter; blend in 4 teaspoons flour, 1/4 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Add 1 cup milk; cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Remove sauce from heat; add 2 ounces Swiss cheese and 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Stir until cheese melts.

title: ice cube punch
directions: Combine sugar and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved.
Cook 5 minutes; cool thoroughly.
Add all fruit juices.
(Fruit juice may be fresh or frozen.)
Pour into 2 ice cube trays and freeze.
Allow 2 cubes per glass; fill with ginger ale.
Can be frozen for day or weeks.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Season and cook hen in enough water so that there will be 1 1/2 quarts broth.
Chop and saute onions and peppers in the 1 1/2 sticks butter.
Cook the vermicelli in the 1 1/2 quarts chicken broth.
When vermicelli is tender, add the onion and pepper mixture to the vermicelli.
(Do not drain off extra broth).
Add mashed Ro-Tel tomatoes with half of the tomato juice.
Add Worcestershire sauce and chopped mushrooms.
Cut Velveeta cheese into cubes and add to mixture.
Stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Add cooked chicken which has been removed from the bones. Pour into casserole dish and bake in 350° oven until bubbly.

title: brenda's crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in crock-pot that has been lightly greased.
Cut thin slices of cheese and put on top.
Cook 3 to 4 hours on low.

title: cherry tarts
directions: Combine and mix until smooth.
Place one vanilla wafer in each cupcake cup.
Fill about half full with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and cover with cherry pie filling.
Makes about 24.

title: broccoli surprise
directions: Mix together in large casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Mix bread crumbs in melted butter and Crisco.
Brown, stirring constantly.
Mix into mashed potatoes; add egg, salt and flour. Form into balls size of small potato. Boil in salted boiling water in large kettle about 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from water and serve.
Good.

title: old fashioned corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425° to 450°.
Place greased iron skillet in hot oven.
Mix dry ingredients; add buttermilk and egg.
Add fat; pour into heated skillet.
Bake for about 20 minutes.
May be baked in iron muffin pans.
Yields 5 to 6 servings of 2 sticks.

title: rye bread
directions: All the ingredients should preferably be at room temperature before baking.
Heat the buttermilk and water until 100°, stir in the yeast and gradually add the salt and flour.
Knead until smooth and shiny, adding a little more water if necessary.
Cover with a damp cloth and leave to rise in a warm place for 2 hours with no draught.

When risen, knead lightly, transfer to a greased form and set aside for 1 hour to rise again, covering with a damp cloth. Brush with water and bake at 400° for about 1 1/4 hours, brushing now and again with water during the baking.
The Aquavit in the dough does not impart any flavor, but helps the bread to remain fresh.

title: yankee pot roast
directions: Brown roast in Dutch oven,
medium
heat for 15 minutes. Add flour and water to make a gravy.
Simmer roast until almost done and then add vegetables.
Cook until tender.

title: best ever french toast
directions: Beat egg.
Add sugar, spices and salt.
Beat well and add evaporated milk.
Beat again.
Dip bread into mixture and fry.
If you have no stale bread, lay out fresh bread and let dry 3 to 4 hours.

title: carrots vichy
directions: Cut carrots 1/8-inch thick.
Melt butter in large skillet. Add water and carrots; cover tightly.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes and test for doneness.
Add sugar, salt, pepper and parsley.
Toss and cook for 1 to 2 minutes more.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Saute pepper and onion in butter until tender.
Boil shrimp and peel.
Cook rice until tender.
Mix all ingredients together and simmer until cheese is melted.
Pout in 3-quart casserole and bake 15 minutes.
I use water if I don't have chicken broth. Also, you can use Cheddar cheese instead of Velveeta.

title: lemon-garlic boiled shrimp
directions: Rinse shrimp with cold water.
Drain and dry on paper towels. Cook garlic in butter until tender.
Remove garlic from pan and add remaining ingredients.
Arrange shrimp in a single layer in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Cover with sauce.
Broil 4 inches from heat for 8 to 10 minutes, depending on their size.
Do not overcook.
Baste with sauce once during boiling.
Sprinkle with parsley just before serving.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: dutch cole slaw
directions: Put cabbage, onions and bell pepper in large bowl.
Sprinkle with sugar and toss well.
Place remaining ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Refrigerate in airtight container.
Slaw may be kept for several weeks and improves with age.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: calico beans with turkey
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Brown turkey and bacon; pour off fat.
Add onions and garlic. Cook slightly. Mix all ingredients together. Pour into casserole and bake for 40 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all together and add 2 cups grated and drained zucchini. Spoon into 2 large or 3 small greased loaf pans.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour or until it tests done.

title: corn crisped chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken pieces.
Crush cornflakes in fine crumbs. Mix crumbs with salt and pepper.
Dip chicken pieces in milk, then roll in seasoned crumbs.
Place chicken pieces, skin side up, in single layer in foil-lined pan.
Do not crowd.
Drizzle with melted margarine or butter.
Bake in 350° oven about 1 hour.
No need to turn chicken while cooking.

title: fajitas with variations
directions: Pound meat with meat mallet to tenderize.
Place in plastic bag.
Combine picante sauce, oil, lemon juice, pepper and garlic powder.
Pour into bag and fasten securely.
Refrigerate 3 to 24 hours, turning several times.
Drain meat, reserving marinade. Place meat on grill over hot coals or on rack of broiler pan. Cook for 5 to 6 minutes on each side or until well done, basting frequently with reserved marinade.
Remove from grill; slice across grain into thin strips.
Place meat on heated tortillas. Top with chunky guacamole and additional picante sauce or whatever you like.
Roll up.
Makes 6 servings.

title: oven baked chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken breast.
Dip each piece in ReaLemon juice.
Sprinkle with Mrs. Dash.
Dip each piece of chicken in cornflakes.
Place in a pan in oven.
Bake approximately 1 hour at 425°.
If cornflakes start getting too brown, cover lightly with aluminum foil.

title: old-fashioned macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine macaroni, butter, 1 cup cheese and seasonings; place in a greased 2-quart baking dish. Combine eggs and milk; pour over macaroni. Do not stir. Sprinkle remaining cheese over top. Bake 40 to 50 minutes. Let set about 5 minutes before serving. Serves 6.

title: shredded beef roast (au jus)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and pour over roast.
Cook in crock-pot for 24 hours on low heat.
Great way to prepare for Sunday dinner in advance.

title: four-layer dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut flour and margarine together like pie crust; stir in nuts.
Press into ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking pan; bake for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: skillet chocolate pie
directions: Mix milk and egg yolks in a heavy iron skillet.
Sift flour, cocoa and sugar.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
Put in a baked 9-inch pie shell.

title: d q coney sauce
directions: Fry and drain meat.
Add rest of the ingredients; simmer. Serve over hot dogs.

title: nut cake
directions: Combine egg yolks, sugar, butter and salt.
Take half of flour and mix with cherries and pecans.
Sift soda and nutmeg with the remaining flour.
Add this to creamed mixture; alternating flour with liquid.
Add cherries and nuts.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold into creamed mixture.
Bake at 250° for 4 hours.
The top will be cracked because of the heavy mixture.

title: meatballs
directions: Shape into balls and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: bacon wrapped bread sticks
directions: Thoroughly mix sugar and chili powder and spread on large dish.
Carefully wrap bread sticks with bacon, leaving both ends open.
Roll in chili/sugar mixture, coating well.
Place in rows on baking tray.
Broil approximately 5 to 10 minutes per side. Watch carefully; they burn easily.

title: trucker beans
directions: Brown meat and drain fat.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a large casserole dish or bean pot.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: pot roast
directions: You will also need an oven cooking bag.

title: barbecued brisket
directions: Marinate brisket in French dressing overnight.
Sprinkle dry onion soup on meat.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 275° for 4 hours or more.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugars, oleo and oil.
Add eggs and cream well.
Add vanilla. Sift flour, cream of tartar and baking soda, add to mixture.
Chill dough.
Roll into tiny balls.
Press with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: pop's shrimp gumbo
directions: Make roux with oil and flour, stirring constantly until dark brown.
Add onion, bell pepper, celery and garlic to roux and wilt vegetables.
Add 2 quarts of water, Ro-Tel tomatoes and fresh tomatoes.
Add seasoning and simmer for about 1 hour.
Add shrimp and crabmeat and continue simmering for 20 minutes.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix everything together except for crackers. Spread crackers on two baking sheets. Pour mixture over crackers.
Let stand for 10 minutes and enjoy.

title: russian tea
directions: Boil cloves in water for 5 minutes.
Add tea bags.
Steep 10 minutes and strain.
Add the lemonade and sugar.
May be weakened with boiling water, if too strong.

title: lemon bars
directions: Combine flour, butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Mix thoroughly. Press into an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: For a one gallon freezer, beat eggs. Add sugar and vanilla, then condensed milk. Mix well. Add enough whole milk to fill the freezer.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat, green pepper and onion.
Drain.
Add chili, beans and tomato juice.
Mix well.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle Fritos over top and sprinkle shredded cheese over the Fritos.
Cover and cook until cheese melts (about 10 minutes).
Serve right from pot!!

title: punch
directions: Remove juice from lemons and oranges. Add pineapple, grape juice and sugar. Add water and cherries, if desired. Makes 50 servings.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar together.
Add dash of salt and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add cake flour that has been sifted.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in tube pan.

title: crispy parmesan chicken tenders
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Line a rimmed baking sheet with foil; coat foil with nonstick spray. Put egg in a shallow bowl; beat lightly with a fork. Put melted butter in another shallow bowl. Mix crushed crackers, paprika, pepper and salt on a sheet of wax paper. Spread Parmesan cheese on another sheet. Dip tenders in egg, then cracker mixture to coat, then dip 1 side in melted butter, then Parmesan cheese. Place cheese side up on lined pan. Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until tenders are golden and cooked through.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix the ingredients and pour into casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and mix with 1 cup crushed cornflakes.
Spread over top and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix kraut, peppers, celery, onions and pimiento.
Combine sugar and vinegar and bring to a boil.
Cool.
Mix all together and let stand covered overnight for best flavor.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix all ingredient together well.

title: aunt grace's punch
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 1/2 qt boiling water.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Let cool.
Mix with pineapple juice and stir. Chill.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.
Add ice or lime sherbet.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: *Use 1 cup evaporated milk (undiluted) and 2 cups plain milk.

title: peanut butter clay
directions: Mix peanut butter with dry milk to taste.
Take peanut butter clay and mold into fun shapes.
Eat clay when play is over.
Drink apple juice with peanut butter to help prevent choking.
Add mini chocolate chips to make more fun.

title: artichoke chili dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; transfer to a baking dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes or until heated through.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Mix ingredients together and put in 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and baking powder. Add milk and beat until all lumps are out. Melt butter in baking dish. Add flour mixture. Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.

title: chuck wagon bean casserole
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a lightly greased 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, stirring once. Sprinkle casserole with crumbled bacon.
Yields 8 servings.

title: milky way cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan. Melt candy bars and butter, stirring frequently, in a large, heavy pan over low heat.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar.
Combine egg yolks, buttermilk and baking soda in a small bowl until blended.
Combine flour and salt.
Add to candy mixture alternately with buttermilk mixture, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Stir in pecans.
In a clean bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 1 1/4 hours or until cake is set and pulls away from sides of pan. Unmold and cool completely.
Melt chocolate in double boiler. Spread over cooled cake.
Yields 16 servings.

title: pea and lettuce salad
directions: Cut lettuce and place in bowl.
Mix in diced onion.
Add frozen peas.
Sprinkle salad dressing mix over peas.
Seal top with mayonnaise.
Refrigerate overnight or 3 to 4 hours.
Mix before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cut up and wash chicken.
In 6-quart pot, place chicken, cover with cold water, add salt and pepper, cook until tender (approximately 45 minutes).
Remove chicken from pot.
Mix flour, cream and melted margarine; stir to mix well.
Dough will be spongy.
Bring broth to rapid boil, lower heat to medium, drop dough mixture by teaspoons into boiling broth; drop in various areas of pot to prevent clumps of dumplings.
Drop dough mixture rapidly, if pot becomes full, discard leftover mixture, do not force into pot; dumplings stick easily.
Cook on low heat after mixture is in pot, for approximately 15 minutes, stir to prevent sticking.
Remove chicken from bone, add meat to cooked dumplings.

title: best broccoli soup
directions: In Dutch oven, bring water to boil.
Add broccoli, celery and carrots.
Boil 2-3 minutes, drain and set aside.
In same kettle, saute onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour to make paste. Gradually add broth and milk, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Add reserved vegetables and remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: gourmet garlic bread(great with salads and pastas)
directions: Slice bread into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Place on cookie sheet. Mix mayonnaise, yogurt and garlic in small bowl until smooth. Spread over bread and sprinkle with Parmesan or Cheddar cheese. Broil 5 minutes or until toasted.
Great with basil sprinkled on top.
Recipe makes 16 servings.
Ultra low-fat.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms with damp paper towels.
Remove stems and reserve for other uses.
Place rack in a large broiler pan; place mushroom caps, stem side up, on rack.
Set aside.
Cook sausage in a large skillet until browned, stirring until it crumbles; drain and return to skillet.
Stir in cream cheese and red pepper. Spoon evenly into mushroom caps; bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Serve immediately.
Yield:
3 1/2 dozen.

title: shrimp stir-fry
directions: In a large pan for stir-frying (or wok) place the kielbasa, sliced thinly.
Add the shrimp.
Cut both peppers into strips. Chop the celery, onion and zucchini (with skin) and combine all vegetables with meats already in pan.
Stir-fry until wanted consistency.
Serve over rice with garlic bread.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all together and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: pecan tassies(makes 24)
directions: Cream together cream cheese and butter.
Stir in flour.
Chill dough 1 hour.
Shape into 2 dozen (1-inch) balls.
Place in ungreased 1 3/4-inch miniature muffin pans.
Press dough against bottom and sides.

title: 7 layer taco dip
directions: Mix together the sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning. Layer all ingredients as listed on a deep plate or shallow dish. Serve with nachos.

title: easy lasagna(microwave)
directions: Crumble ground beef in large bowl.
Cook at High 3 to 4 minutes, or until beef is browned; stir once.
Drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Meanwhile, combine Ricotta cheese, Romano cheese, egg and pepper.
Spoon 1/2 cup sauce in 12 x 8-inch dish; alternately layer noodles, egg mixture, Mozzarella cheese and sauce, forming 3 layers.
Cover completely with plastic wrap. Cook at High 8 minutes and at Medium-low 32 to 34 minutes, or until noodles are tender.
If necessary, shield ends of dish with foil, during last 10 minutes of cooking. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese; let stand, covered, 15 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Mix well the first 4 ingredients.
Add water; knead until dough is soft and elastic like bread dough.
Roll out in 1 big piece, then cut lengthwise and crosswise into pieces.
Deep fry at high heat (375°).

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In large bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.

Add peanut butter and beat. Gradually beat in milk and vanilla. Fold in topping; pour into crust and sprinkle with nuts. Cover and freeze at least 4 hours. Let stand at room temperature for about 15 minutes before serving.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt butter in large saucepan over low heat.
Add the marshmallows and stir with a wooden spoon until they are melted.
Take pan off heat.
Add cereal and stir quickly until all cereal is coated.
Spread mixture in pan and press down firmly.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix sour cream and pudding together.
Drain oranges, fruit cocktail and pineapple.
Save the pineapple juice.
Mix fruit with the sour cream mixture, then add a little pineapple juice.
Add marshmallows and enough Cool Whip to make it thick.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix shortening, white sugar, brown sugar, eggs and other ingredients.
Roll into a ball and flatten with a glass.
Put sugar on top if you like.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken ravioli
directions: Boil chicken in large covered pan.
Remove chicken from broth; cool.
Debone and cut up as for salad.
Saute pepper and onion in skillet with butter; strain broth.
Bring to boil and add noodles; cook until done.
Add chopped chicken and all remaining ingredients and seasonings.
Mix thoroughly.
Place in casserole dish and heat in oven until cheese is well melted.
It can be cooked at a very low temperature on stove top.
Serve warm.

title: date pudding
directions: Pour boiling water and 1 teaspoon soda over dates.
Mix nuts, egg, sugar and flour together.
Add dates.
In baking pan add brown sugar and water.
Let come to a boil.
Add date mixture. Bake 30 minutes in 375° oven.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: rocky road candy(kid recipe)
directions: Mix chocolate chips, milk and margarine.
Heat until chocolate chips and margarine are melted.
Heat in microwave or double boiler.
Stir in nuts and marshmallows.
Line a cookie sheet with wax paper.
Drop candy by spoonfuls.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: city tuna sandwich
directions: Amounts will vary according to number of people being served.

title: beef pie
directions: Saute hamburger, onion and garlic clove.
Add salt, pepper and paprika to season.
Drain hamburger and return to skillet.
Add barbecue sauce.
Roll bread dough out flat.
Grease a shallow quiche dish or pie pan.
Place dough in the bottom of the pan and work into sides of pan.
Pour hamburger into dough and top with cheese.
Fold the remaining edges of the dough up onto the top of the dish and pinch together.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove cover 10 minutes before done to allow for browning of crust.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Mix sugar and milk in saucepan.
Bring to boil, then add soda. Cook
until
mixture
turns brown.
Remove from heat and add pecans
and vanilla. Beat until creamy and glossy.
Drop by spoonfuls
onto
wax
paper.
After it sets, cools and hardens, wrap
individually
in
wax paper.
Keep wrapped until ready to serve.
May be kept in airtight container.

title: artichoke squares
directions: Drain artichoke hearts and save the marinade.
Chop up the artichokes.
Saute the onion in the marinade.
Combine eggs with breadcrumbs.
Add everything else and pour into a 7 x 11-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: spiced cider
directions: In a large saucepan, heat cider and cinnamon stick to boiling. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Uncover.
Stir in remaining ingredients except orange slices and cloves. Simmer 5 minutes longer. Serve in heat tempered punch bowl or crock-pot. Float orange slices studded with whole cloves.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and eggs.
Add flour and frosting mix; beat well.
Stir in the nuts of your choice.
Pour into a very well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 60 to 65 minutes.
Cool cake 1 hour, then remove from pan.
Allow to cool completely before cutting.
Don't cheat!
Please don't cut before it's completely cool.

title: kielbasa, fried cabbage and noodles
directions: Broil kielbasa and cut up into chunks.
Shred cabbage and fry slowly with onion until soft.
Add salt, pepper and sugar.
Boil noodles in salt water and drain.
Add noodles and meat to cabbage mixture and mix well.
Fry at medium heat for 1/2 hour.

title: linguini salad
directions: Cook linguini until done.
Add salad dressing and Salad Supreme while hot.
Add onion, tomatoes and cucumber.
Serve at room temperature.
Great for picnics.

title: baked halibut olympia
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sour cream.
Spread mixture on top of halibut.
Top with onion, Parmesan cheese and cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until halibut flakes with fork.
Enjoy!

title: holiday pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add next ingredients.
Stir in pecans and raisins. Put in unbaked pie shell and bake for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: almond coffee
directions: Add almond extract to coffee.
Shake in a plastic bag to coat thoroughly.
Store in refrigerator.
Brew according to package directions.
Enjoy!

title: oatmeal flake cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg, water and vanilla, blending well.
Resift flour with salt and soda and add to creamed mixture.
Blend in rolled oats and cereal flakes.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cheese and sausage dip
directions: In crock-pot, cook sausage and drain.
Add other ingredients. When cheese is melted, just simmer. Ready to serve.

title: spanish green beans
directions: Saute bacon, onion and green pepper until lightly brown.
Add flour; stir until smooth.
Heat tomatoes; add salt.
Add gradually to bacon, onion and green pepper.
Gently stir in green beans. Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: lady baltimore cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 8 x 1 1/2-inch or 9 x 1 1/2-inch round layer pans.
Prepare, bake and cool cake as directed on package.

title: payday cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and bake in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan for 12 to 18 minutes at 350°.
When baked and still hot, put 3 cups miniature marshmallows on top.
Heat remaining ingredients until smooth, stirring constantly, then add Rice Krispies and salted cocktail peanuts.
Spread on top of marshmallows.
Cool several hours.

title: granny's icebox cookies
directions: Mix sugar, Crisco, eggs and vanilla together.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Take cookie dough and divide in half.
Roll each half in wax paper.
Chill dough for 1 hour, then slice 1/2-inch slices.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes until golden brown.

title: just rolls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in bowl. Cool to lukewarm. Add beaten eggs, yeast and flour.
Knead. Form into balls and let rise until double in bulk.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry jello mold
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 1/2 cups of boiling water.
Add all ingredients, except for sour cream.
Pour half of mixture in mold and let set in refrigerator.
Leave the other half outside.
When refrigerated mix is set firm, spread sour cream over top and pour the rest of the mixture on top.
Put back in refrigerator.
When mold is set, spread Cool Whip on top and garnish with chopped nuts.

title: fast and easy jambalaya
directions: Sprinkle lemon pepper and garlic powder over chicken cubes. Heat oil in large skillet or 3-quart saucepan over medium-high heat.
Cook seasoned chicken in oil for 5 minutes or until no longer pink (stir frequently).
Add onions and sausage.
Cook an additional 5 minutes, stir occasionally.
Stir in picante sauce and tomatoes.
Reduce heat to medium and cook 12 minutes.
Add peas and cook an additional 2 to 3 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Serve over cooked rice.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: pumpkin cheesecake bars
directions: Combine flour and brown sugar in medium bowl.
Cut in butter to make a crumb mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Set aside 3/4 cup mixture for topping.
Press remaining mixture into bottom of 8 x 8 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Cool slightly.

title: grilled fennel burger
directions: Mix meats, egg, crumbs and seasonings; pat in ten 1/2-inch patties.
Broil over hot coals, turning once, 15 to 20 minutes total time or until meat is done.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Place peeled, sliced apples in unbaked pie crust.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over apples.
Top with crust.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pickled bologna
directions: Layer bologna and onions, starting with bologna and ending with onions, in 1 1/2-quart glass casserole with cover.
Combine remaining ingredients, using more or less vinegar and water, depending on taste, and pour over bologna and onions.
Let stand; cover ajar, for 12 to 18 hours at room temperature, then cover completely and refrigerate.
Should stand a couple of days all together.
Serve with assorted crackers and cheeses.

title: asparagus spoon bread(yields 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.
In a medium-sized saucepan, heat milk slowly.
Add cornmeal and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until soft and thickened, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar, salt, margarine, baking powder and cheese.
Beat until cheese melts. When cooled, stir in egg yolks one at a time.

title: crispy peanut butter balls
directions: Melt peanut butter and butter together in a medium saucepan. Remove from heat. Pour in sugar and Rice Krispies. Mix well and chill.
Roll into desirable balls.
"Ready to eat".

title: marinated vegetable salad dijon
directions: In a large bowl, combine mustard, oil, vinegar, scallions, basil, pepper and sugar.
Mix in mushrooms, tomatoes and artichokes.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight.
Spoon over a bed of watercress.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: christmas m&m's cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Beat together butter, brown sugar and white sugar in a large bowl until light and fluffy. Blend in eggs and vanilla. Combine flour, salt and baking soda in a small bowl. Add to butter mixture. Mix well. Add M&M's. Drop by teaspoons and bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mack's cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, Accent, scallions and 1/2 of the shredded dried beef.
Mix well and shape into a ball.
Roll in remaining dried beef.
Chill.

title: veronica's veal scaloppine
directions: Cut partially frozen veal cutlets into bite-size pieces.
Melt butter in a Dutch oven.
Flour veal and brown in butter.
Remove meat to bowl and reserve.
Add onion and garlic to butter; brown several seconds.
Then add sliced mushrooms.
Return meat to pot; add tomato sauce, hot water, oregano, basil, 1/2 cup wine and grated cheese.
Serve over pasta.
Grate additional cheese and some fresh parsley.
Serve with hot baked garlic bread.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook hamburger meat and drain.
Drain green beans and set aside.
Combine the 3 soups with 2 cans of water and mix together. Peel and slice potatoes.
In rectangle pan, put a layer of hamburger meat, then layer of potatoes, then 1 can of green beans. Repeat layers.
Pour soup mixture over.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 45 minutes or until potatoes are done, then top with onion rings and bake for 15 minutes more.

title: "pretend" orange julius
directions: Combine orange juice, milk, water, sugar, vanilla, Secret Mix and ice cubes in blender container.
Blend until mixed but ice crystals remain.
Serve immediately.
Makes about 4 1/2 cups.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Melt butter; add milk.
Heat to scalding.
Beat eggs slightly; add sugar and vanilla and swirl into milk.
Strain into a 9-inch pastry lined pan.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 470° for 10 minutes, then at 375° for 10 minutes.
(Brush crust with unbeaten egg white before adding custard mix.)

title: baked ham
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line large pan with aluminum foil. Cover ham on all sides with jelly.
Place on foil.
Pour Coke over ham.
Wrap foil around ham and seal it.
Pour water in pan under the foil.
Cook for 3 1/2 hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except stuffing and butter.
Line casserole dish with stuffing.
Pour in squash mixture.
Sprinkle with more herb stuffing; dot with butter.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: marshmallow creme dip
directions: Put softened cream cheese in mixing bowl.
Add Marshmallow Creme and using wire whip mix well.
Put in airtight container and refrigerate.
Use on apples, strawberries or any fruit.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs, and vanilla.
Mix well. Fold in zucchini and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: heath bars
directions: Line a jelly roll pan that's greased with crackers.
In a saucepan, bring to boil sugar and oleo or butter.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Pour over crackers and spread.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Put candy bars on; melt and spread.
After the chocolate is set, break into pieces.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Don't separate.
Push out onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until golden.
Cool.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and add spaghetti sauce.
After boiling noodles, lay one layer of noodles, then mixture of sauce.
Add one layer of each cheese on top.
Add another layer of noodles and another layer of each cheese.
Bake at 350° until all cheeses are melted and lasagna is bubbling.
Let cool until desired temperature and serve.

title: ginger-cocoa crisps
directions: Cream shortening; gradually add 1 cup sugar, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add egg and beat well.
Stir
in
molasses.
Sift
flour and cocoa together; stir in soda,
ginger
and
salt.
Add
to
creamed mixture, stirring well.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix well; form into small balls.
Arrange in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: ala rice
directions: Cook rice in water (approximately 4 cups) until fluffy.
Add Lipton soup and water.
When bubbling, add drained mushrooms and drained peas.
Heat all and serve.

title: beer fish batter
directions: Combine all ingredients.
If batter is too thick, use water to thin.
Dip fish in batter and deep fry in hot oil.
Delicious with all vegetables:
broccoli, peppers, parsley, mushrooms, onions, etc.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Boil vegetable for 10 minutes; drain. Add 1/2 stick of margarine and cheese whiz. Pour in casserole dish. For topping; melt 1 stick of margarine, add crackers and sprinkle over vegetable mixture. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Pour into casserole and top with the crackers which are mixed with the margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Cool.
Combine with other ingredients and mix well.
Best if chilled before serving.

title: chocolate cream roll
directions: Beat yolks with 1/2 cup sugar and cocoa, fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Line well-greased biscuit pan with wax paper, brush with butter or oil.
Pour mixture on this.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Turn out on a towel; roll as a jelly roll.
When cold, unroll and spread with whipped cream sweetened with powdered sugar. Roll, slice and serve with hot chocolate sauce.

title: aunt nedia's carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar and eggs until creamy.
Add cooking oil and grated carrots.
Add flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix for 2 minutes, then add cinnamon.
Pour into two 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: beef chowder
directions: Combine celery, meat, onion and sliced potatoes in a baking pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.
Cool 2 cups of noodles.
Mix all together and add soup, Milnot and cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted and season to taste.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix together.
Just before serving, add one 12-ounce package of Fritos corn chips and 1 bottle Catalina dressing.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburg; drain.
Add onions; cook to soft.
Add remaining items and simmer for 1 hour.

title: tuna burgers
directions: In a bowl, combine tuna, bread crumbs, celery, mayonnaise, onion, chili sauce and egg.
Shape into 4 patties.
Melt butter in a skillet; cook patties for about 4 to 5 minutes per side or until lightly browned.
Serve on buns with lettuce and tomatoes.

title: house special tea
directions: Brew a quart of tea. Pour in pitcher. Combine other ingredients. Stir and serve.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients together except peanut butter and vanilla and cook until soft ball stage.
Then add peanut butter and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Pour into buttered dish and let cool.

title: grammy's chocolate chip snack
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, mix 1 stick melted butter and 1 crushed package of graham crackers to form crust.

title: bible cake(king james version)
directions: Mix as you would any other cake.
Bake in moderate 325° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Use tube or Bundt pan.

title: caramel corn
directions: Cook brown sugar, syrup, butter and salt at 245°.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Add flavoring and baking soda; beat.
Pour over corn. Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: mexican shells
directions: Cook shells by directions (drain).
Brown hamburger meat (drain excess fat).

Mix picante sauce, tomato sauce and water together. Add 1/2 cup sauce mix, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/4 cup onions to meat. Pour half of remaining sauce into bottom of 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish. Stuff shells and put into dish.
Pour remainder of sauce over shells.
Bake shells (covered) 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and top with remainder of cheese and add onions.
Return to oven just to brown onions and melt cheese.

title: homemade soup
directions: Can use stew beef, but cook for 3 to 4 hours (separately).

title: morning casserole
directions: Brown sausages and cut into 1/4-inch pieces.
Cube bread and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread sausages and cheese over bread. Add milk to beaten eggs and pour over bread mixture.
Spread undiluted soup over the top.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: cantaloupe ice pops
directions: You will need 12 plastic cups or popsicle molds (3 ounces each), and 12 popsicle sticks.

title: date muffins
directions: Mix all.
Bake in muffin tins at 325° for 15 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Combine beef, bacon and onion in skillet.
Cook over medium heat until meat is browned.
Drain off grease.
Add soup, salt and paprika to skillet; mix well.
Continue cooking 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in sour cream; heat but do not boil. Serve over noodles or rice.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: cranberry coffeecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch sheet cake pan. In large bowl, cream butter.
Gradually add sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix in almond extract.
Stir in flour alternately with sour cream.
Pour into prepared pan.
Spoon cranberry sauce evenly over batter; spread slightly, but do not try to cover batter. Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until cake pulls away from sides of pan . Drizzle with glaze.
Cut into squares.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, butter, eggs, brown sugar, salt and spices; mix well. Add juice, blending until smooth.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Top with marshmallows and bake until just melted.
Yields 8 servings.

title: spaghetti bravisimo
directions: In large saucepan, combine onion soup mix and spaghetti with water; cook 20 minutes or until spaghetti is tender.
Do not drain. In large skillet, brown meat; stir in tomato sauce and paste, parsley, oregano and basil.
Add to onion soup-spaghetti in the saucepan and heat through.
Makes approximately 4 servings.

title: sweet potato a-mode
directions: Mix together.
Serve over warm oatmeal cookie.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: french toast
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl, slowly stir in milk and add eggs one at a time to mix.
Should be the consistency of a pancake batter.
May add a little more milk if desired.
After batter is ready, sprinkle nutmeg lightly over batter.
Dip dry bread slices in batter and cook in a lightly greased electric skillet or frying pan over a slow heat.
Allow to brown on both sides.

title: lazy man's cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Pour into pan on top of margarine.
Add fruit (juice and all) up and down flour mixture, not going to edges.
Do not stir. (Crust will bake over fruit.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: strawberry-banana salad
directions: To mix gelatin, add thawed strawberries, pineapple and nuts. Pour 1/2 mixture into container. Congeal. Spread sour cream over. Slice bananas over sour cream. Cover with rest of strawberry mixture and congeal. Serves 8.

title: tossed baked chicken
directions: Cut up frying chicken into 8 pieces or quarters if small. Rinse and leave wet.
In a bowl, mix seasonings.
Coat chicken well.
Place coated chicken in oven-safe pan.
Do not overlap pieces.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on chicken.
Bake until brown in 400° to 450° oven.
If chicken seems dry, add a little barbecue sauce or water.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Reduce oven to 250° or 300°.
Bake until done, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: oven fried parmesan chicken
directions: Combine the corn flakes, Parmesan cheese, garlic salt or powder, parsley flakes and pepper.
Dip chicken in butter, then dip in crumb mixture.
Place on a greased shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: monkey bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease 12-inch tube pan.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Working with 1 can at a time, remove biscuits, separate and cut each one into 4 pieces.
Coat with butter, add to bag of sugar mixture.
Shake to coat.
Gently press pieces into prepared pan.
Repeat with remaining cans of biscuits. Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until brown and toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook on low heat until forms a syrup.
Add 1 cup marshmallows. Continue cooking until melted.
(You may want to finish in the oven at 350°, it will scorch easily.)

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Stir well.
Then roll into small balls.
Place on well-greased cookie sheet.
With a fork, press balls of mixture down.
Bake at 350° or 400° until golden brown.
Sprinkle small amount of white sugar on top of cookie while still hot.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients well.
Add shrimp (make sure shrimp is thawed and squeeze all excess water out of shrimp).
Chill overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: mango nut bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Stir in dry ingredients, mango and lime juice.
Mix all together, add nuts.
Bake in loaf pan at 375° for 1 hour.
Do not cut until next day for firmness.

title: reese cup candy
directions: Mix sugar, butter and peanut butter with mixer.
Roll mixture into balls on waxed paper.

title: real chile verde
directions: Cover bottom of large pot with oil and warm.
Cube pork; mince garlic and chop onion.
Put pork, garlic, 1/4 of onion and desired salt in pot and brown; sprinkle 2 tablespoons of flour while stirring and browning meat.
When brown, turn down heat.
Chop tomatoes and chilies and add with the rest of the onion to the meat; add 1 quart of water and boil.
Boil water out 3 times or until all ingredients are very soft.
Lower heat when thick or add cornstarch.
Great on burritos, eggs, fried potatoes, rice.

title: blue ribbon banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl, mix pudding and milk.
Beat until pudding sets.
Add sour cream and blend well.
Add Cool Whip and blend. Add Eagle Brand milk, if desired (and it is yummy with it), and blend well.

title: surprise muffins
directions: Beat together and pour into muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: polynesian cake
directions: Combine all the dry ingredients.
Combine all the wet ingredients.
Mix together, alternately adding dry and wet ingredients. Pour batter into large tube pan (10-inch).
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.
(Might need 5 or 10 minutes more.)
Check with cake tester.
Bake at 350°.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown first 5 ingredients and drain.
Put tomato sauce, tomato paste and Italian seasoning on simmer while you prepare noodles. Don't overcook noodles all of the way.
Set noodles aside.
Put meat on low.
Take 9 x 13-inch pan, line with noodles, meat sauce mixture, then a thin layer of Ricotta cheese, then Mozzarella cheese; last ingredient before repeat.
Top layer:
Ricotta cheese next to noodles and meat mixture and cover with Mozzarella and thin layer of Parmesan cheese.
Bake for how long it takes for it to get brown in 350° to 400° oven.

title: the best ribs u ever ate
directions: Cook the ribs on a broiler pan filled with about 1/2 inch of water.
Lay out the ribs on the broiler and sprinkle with garlic salt.
Cover ribs with aluminum foil, sealing around the edges so that the steam helps to cook the meat.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours at 350° in oven, then take out of oven, remove the foil and turn the ribs over.
Sprinkle with garlic salt, check the water level in the bottom of the broiler, re-cover with foil and cook for another 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
It seems like a long time, but it's right way to do it!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Beat egg and mix with soup, salt and pepper.
Add cheese and mayonnaise.
Mix in with broccoli.
Put in casserole and cover with more Swiss cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tangy italian dressing
directions: Combine ingredients and stir until blended.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze.

title: baked apples with cinnamon sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash and core apples.
Starting at stem end, pare apples 1/3 of the way down (this helps keep skins from bursting).
Place in shallow baking pan, pared sides up.
Boil water, sugar and cinnamon for 10 minutes over medium heat.
Pour over apples.
Bake about 1 hour or until easily pierced with fork (spoon syrup over apples frequently during baking to glaze). Serve warm with cream or ice cream.

title: 7-minute frosting
directions: Combine in top of double boiler.
Cook over rapidly boiling water.
Beat with a rotary beater or electric mixer until mixture stands in peaks.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla; continue beating until thick enough to spread.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Pat hamburger in bottom of casserole dish.
Place sliced onions over meat.
Mix beans and soup; pour over onions.
Cover with Tater Tots.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling and keep warm, but not bubbling.
May be made ahead of time and actually improves with standing and reheating.

title: martha jane's sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Beat in vanilla and buttermilk.
Combine dry ingredients and blend in slowly.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on a cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 48 cookies.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Place all ingredients into a large container.
Stir until all are blended together.
Store into airtight container until ready to use.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly with electric mixer so mixture will not be grainy.
Cook, add vanilla and eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Pour in baked pie shell and cover with whipped cream.
Chill a few hours before serving. Toasted coconut may be sprinkled over whipped cream.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into pie shells.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken filling dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together in casserole dish and place buttered bread crumbs on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour if cold.
If ingredients are warm, bake until slightly brown.

title: quarterback scramble
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Melt butter in large shallow 15 x 10 x 2-inch roasting pan in oven.
Remove.
Stir in seasoning packet. Add cereal and nuts.
Mix until all pieces are coated.
Bake in oven for 45 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Add beef jerky and cheese.
Stir to coat evenly.
Bake an additional 15 minutes. Spread on absorbent paper to cool.
Makes 9 1/2 cups.

title: cheese cake cupcakes
directions: Line a 24-muffin tin with cupcake liners.
Place one vanilla wafer in each one.
Blend sugar, cream cheese, lemon juice, eggs and vanilla in bowl.
Spoon in each tin to about half full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Top each with a spoonful of cherry pie filling.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Combine brown sugar, cinnamon and 1/2 cup of pecans in a small bowl.
Set aside. Combine cake mix, salad oil, sugar, vanilla, eggs and sour cream. Beat two minutes at medium speed.
Stir in 1/2 cup pecans.
Pour half of batter into prepared pan.
Sprinkle with half of brown sugar mixture.
Pour remaining batter in pan and sprinkle with remaining brown sugar mixture.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into balls.
Brown in pan and drain.
Place in baking dish.
Combine 1 can of cream of mushroom soup and 1/2 cup water.
Add to meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: edith's favorite frosting(creamy chocolate)
directions: Cook cocoa, sugar and cornstarch, plus 1 cup boiling water, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat and add rest of ingredients.
Pour on cake.
You can spread on cake right out of the oven.
Makes 2 cups.

title: macaroni salad for a crowd
directions: Mix all ingredients except macaroni.
Add drained, cooled macaroni and mix.
Add more Miracle Whip if too dry.
This is best if made the day before eaten.
Spice amounts may vary according to your taste.
Flavor greatly enhances overnight.

title: hamburger corn-pone
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Add seasonings and tomatoes. Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add kidney beans.
Pour mixture into 2-quart casserole dish.
Spread corn bread batter over top.
Bake at 425° until corn bread is brown.

title: pecan sticks
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and nuts, vanilla and salt; then flour sifted with baking powder. Bake 30 minutes in moderate oven; cool and cut into sticks or squares.

title: crab puffs
directions: Drain crab meat.
Mix all ingredients in bowl; spread on English muffins.
Cut muffins into quarters.
Broil 5 to 7 minutes. Can be frozen 3 to 4 months.

title: texas chocolate cake
directions: Bring to boil butter, water and cocoa.
Mix together sugar, flour, soda and salt.
Pour hot liquid into flour mixture and beat well.
Add eggs and beat.
Add sour cream and beat.
Pour into greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: 3 pecan pies
directions: Mix sugar, melted butter, Karo, flour and vanilla.
Stir in eggs, one at a time.
Do not beat.
Add pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until firm.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix flour, salt, sugar and cinnamon.
Pour over apples in pie crust and add butter on top.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake immediately.

title: biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients.
May need more milk to make a sticky dough.
Roll out dough and cut into biscuit shape.
Bake 375° for 15-20 mins.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Beat eggs. Add salt, pepper, oil, cheese, garlic, onion and parsley. Mix flour and baking powder together. Add to egg mixture, then fold in zucchini. Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes. Cut into 2 x 2-inch squares.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Peel, dice, cook and cool potatoes (seasoned); set aside. Cook and crumble bacon; set aside.
Combine all ingredients; mix lightly.
Bake casserole dish uncovered at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Fry beef and onion until it loses its pink color.
Add enchilada sauce, salt, pepper, water, soup and green chilies.
In a 2-quart casserole layer tortillas and meat mixture and cheese. Bake at 350° until hot through.

title: peanut butter puffs
directions: Measure Cocoa Puffs into large bowl.
Set aside.
Bring sugar, syrup and honey to rolling boil.
Add peanut butter.
Stir until smooth.
Pour over cereal.
Stir until well coated.
Shape into small balls and place on wax paper to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Fill a large salad bowl with shredded lettuce.
(Slice like cabbage to make it more fluffy.)
Add in layers the celery, green pepper and onion.
Cook the frozen peas and allow to cool, then add to salad in layers again:
peas and mayonnaise.
Sprinkle sugar over dressing.
Use cheese to cover salad.
Sprinkle bacon bits on top.
Cover with plastic wrap. Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix half of strawberries, cut up, with sugar, water and cornstarch.
Cook over medium heat 2 to 3 minutes.
Cut remaining berries and put in bottom of baked pie shell.
As mixture cools, pour over berries.
Top with whipped cream and garnish with a few berries.
Refrigerate a few hours before serving.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Pour the chicken broth into a medium saucepan.
Stir in the noodles and carrots.
Bring to a simmer over high heat, about 2 minutes.

title: grandma's special cheese ball
directions: Have all cheese at room temperature.
Blend the 3 cheeses, grated onion, Worcestershire sauce, 1/4 cup parsley and 1/4 cup nuts.
When everything is blended, make into a ball and roll in the other 1/4 cup parsley and 1/4 cup nuts.
When ball is well coated with parsley and nuts, wrap in foil and refrigerate for several hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix preceding ingredients and in greased muffin pan, cook at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes until light brown.
Makes 6.

title: crepes a la florence
directions: You will need an 8 or 9-inch saute pan.

title: ann's peach cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, flour and butter.
Put peaches in a 2-quart casserole dish, then put mixture over peaches.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: tea time tassies
directions: Blend cream cheese with 1/2 cup butter; then stir in flour. Refrigerate dough.
Heat oven to 375°.
Shape dough into 24 balls. Place one in each cup of greased mini muffin pans.
Press dough to bottom and sides of each cup.
In a small bowl beat 1 tablespoon butter, egg, brown sugar, vanilla and salt until smooth.
Divide pecans into half.
Use half to sprinkle on bottom of pastry-lined muffin pans.
Fill each with about 1 teaspoon egg mixture.
Top with rest of pecans.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool, then carefully remove from pans.
Makes 24 cookies.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook mixed vegetables according to directions; drain. Add next 4 ingredients; mix well. Spoon into lightly greased 2-quart shallow baking dish. Sprinkle crumbs over top and drizzle with margarine. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle vegetables with garlic salt if desired.

title: baked chicken parmesan
directions: Mix equal parts of Parmesan and lemon pepper. Roll chicken in cheese, then butter and back to cheese.
Place on baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Saute onion and bell pepper; add to meat.
Season meat mixture with a little sugar, basil and salt to taste.
Pour tomatoes, tomato sauce and tomato paste over meat mixture and simmer.
Cook macaroni in salted water according to package directions and drain.
While macaroni is hot, add sour cream and cream cheese.
Stir until melted.
Pour over meat mixture in buttered casserole.
Grate cheese and sprinkle on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: crawfish, shrimp or crab etouffee
directions: Melt butter; saute onion, bell pepper and jalapeno.
Add soup and let cook on medium heat for 10 minutes.
Add meat; season to taste with Cajun seasoning, salt, pepper and Tabasco or Louisiana hot sauce.
Add garlic last.
Cook 10 minutes on medium heat; let set 10
minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: italian vegetable casserole
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
Add vegetables 3 minutes before pasta is finished.
Drain.
Toss with Italian dressing. Put into casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Salt chicken and then dip in beaten egg that a little water has been added.
Then roll chicken in a mixture of the potato flakes and Parmesan cheese.
Put in baking dish skin side up, uncovered.
Bake 30 minutes.
Turn over and bake 30 minutes more.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix the sugar, flour, salt and soda. Melt margarine, cocoa, oil and water. Add the eggs and buttermilk. Bake in oiled sheet pan at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Cool and frost.

title: nana's sausage balls
directions: Brown sausage.
Mix sausage and cheese together.
Slowly add Bisquick and knead together by hand.
Add water if too dry.
Roll into balls and bake on cookie sheet at 350° for approximately 10 minutes, until brown.
Freezes well, then just warm in the microwave.

title: turkey chow mein
directions: In large skillet, stir-fry green pepper and celery in butter until tender-crisp.
Combine cornstarch, water and soy sauce; blend into pepper mixture.
Stir in bouillon.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Stir in remaining ingredients except noodles.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve over noodles.
Serves 6.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook chicken in water until tender.
Remove meat from bones. Add vegetables, seasonings and noodles.
Simmer until done.
Add water as needed.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together ingredients, except cheese.
Pour 1/2 batter in dish or pan.
Put 1/2 cheese on top.
Pour rest of batter and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: old settler's beans
directions: Fry sausage and hamburg.
Drain grease.
Add all other ingredients and stir.
Let simmer until hot.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all except cheese in 1 1/2-quart greased casserole. Put cheese on top and bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Crush 1/2 berries.
Add sugar and cornstarch.
Dissolve gelatine in lemon juice and cook over low heat until thick and transparent.
Cool.
Quarter remaining berries and fold into cooled mixture.
Spoon into baked pie shell and top with whipped cream.

title: applesauce fruit cake
directions: Mix sugar, Crisco and eggs together.
Sift flour, spices and salt.
Dust raisins and nuts with mixture.
Heat applesauce with soda and when it bubbles up, fold in with dry ingredients.
Then mix in pineapple and beat with electric mixer.
Add other fruits. Bake 1 1/2 hours in tube pan.
Turn off oven and leave cake in for about 10 minutes.
Let cool and then remove from pan.
Freezes very well.

title: zucchini combo
directions: Slice zucchini and combine with mushrooms in a 1 1/2-quart glass casserole.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and salt.
Dot with butter.
Microwave, covered, for 7 to 8 minutes or until zucchini is tender.
Stir in tomatoes and cheese.
Microwave, covered, for 2 to 3 minutes, or until hot and cheese is melted.
Very colorful, delicious dish.

title: chicken fingers
directions: In a small bowl, combine sesame seed and Parmesan cheese. Roll chicken pieces in sesame mixture.
Heat oil in ovenproof heavy-bottomed nonstick skillet or saute pan, until just below smoking point.
Add chicken strips and brown on both sides over medium-high heat; do not scorch.
Place chicken strips on cookie sheet and bake in preheated 425° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until cooked through.
To serve, arrange chicken strips on plates with lettuce leaves and garnish with orange rind.
Serve with honey-mustard sauce.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and dry orange Jell-O well.
Add other ingredients; mix.
Chill and serve.

title: green beans surprise
directions: Cook beans slowly with no seasonings.
Saute onions in margarine (1 stick) until soft.
Add to beans, along with cheese and soup.
Crumble crackers in remaining 1 stick of margarine until completely absorbed.
Place bean mixture in greased pan and sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: smoked turkey
directions: Place turkey in 5 gallon bucket.
Add spices and enough water to cover turkey completely.
Marinate for 5 days (keep cool; add ice cubes if necessary).
Wrap in foil with small hole at each end.
Smoke over very low fire (keep temperature under 200°) for 16 hours.
Remove foil and glaze with:

title: banana bars
directions: Line 15 x 13 pan with whole graham crackers.
Sprinkle 4 1/2 oz. slivered or sliced almonds over them.
Boil: 1 3/4 sticks butter and 2/3 cup brown sugar for 2 minutes from the time it starts to bubble.
Spoon over crackers and nuts.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Cut while still slightly warm.

title: autumn corn muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl; do not overmix.
Fill muffin cups high.
They will rise slightly.
You can use cupcake paper cups.
Bake in hot oven (425°) until done (about 20 to 25 minutes).
Makes 1 dozen.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter with electric beater until smooth. Beat eggs in separate bowl with electric beater for 30 seconds. Add eggs to butter and sugar mixture.
Alternate milk and flour to mixture, adding a little at a time.
Blend very well.
Add lemon extract.
Continue to beat for another 2 minutes.
Place batter in greased and floured Bundt pan.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour, then another 15 minutes at 350°.

title: baked spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook and stir ground beef, onion and garlic powder until brown, drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour; stir.
Serve over spaghetti noodles. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: mint tea
directions: Pour boiling water over tea, sugar and mint; let cool. Strain, add fruit juices and enough water to make a gallon. Serve over crushed ice.

title: sour cream raisins
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Raisins last.
Pour into 8-inch or 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then bake at 325° for 35 minutes longer.
Test with knife, done when comes out clean.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Allow butter to soften, but not melt (leave out for 2 hours at room temperature or use Low power on microwave carefully).
In large mixing bowl, blend sugar into butter.
Blend in 1 cup of flour.
Add orange juice and blend.
Blend in second cup of flour. Add vanilla.
Blend in chocolate chips in quantity as desired.

title: mushroom rolls
